-- Generated from selected Hangzhou markdown files (with cover images)
WITH input_rows(attraction_name_zh, sort_order, name_en, name_zh, body, cover_image_path) AS (
  VALUES
  ('法喜寺', 0, 'Faxisi Mountain Gate (Shanmen)', '法喜寺山门', '<p>The Shanmen (Mountain Gate) of Faxisi is located at 338 Tianzhu Road, Xihu District, Hangzhou. It is the main entrance of the largest and oldest temple among Hangzhou''s Three Tianzhu Temples. The Shanmen is a typical Jiangnan Buddhist building in Ming-Qing style, with three bays and a single-eave xieshan roof with upturned eaves. Horizontal plaques inscribed "Faxisi" and "Shangtianzhu Preaching Temple" are hung under the eaves, presenting a dignified aura. A pair of stone lions stand on both sides of the gate, with bluestone slab steps laid in front——ascending the steps, one''s mind naturally calms. Inside the gate are enshrined statues of the Four Heavenly Kings, symbolizing "favorable weather for crops." The Four Heavenly Kings each hold a precious treasure with majestic expressions, forming the best-preserved set among Hangzhou temple mountain gates. Visitors entering the temple through this gate are first greeted by ancient ginkgo trees and curling incense smoke, with the sound of bells and Buddhist chants drifting in the wind, instantly evoking a sense of tranquility. Faxisi is popularly renowned among the people as "the most effective temple for seeking marriage," therefore the area in front of the Shanmen is perennially crowded with pilgrims.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_faxi_temple_sa_01.png'),
  ('法喜寺', 1, 'Hall of Heavenly Kings (Tianwang Dian)', '天王殿', '<p>The Hall of Heavenly Kings is the first main hall after the Shanmen of Faxisi and the first hall on the central axis of the temple. The hall spans five bays in width and four bays in depth, with a single-eave xieshan roof covered with blue-gray tubular tiles, and layered brackets under the eaves——rigorous structure and magnificent bearing. Enshrined in the center of the hall is the incarnation of Maitreya Bodhisattva——the big-bellied, bare-chested, and ever-smiling Maitreya Buddha statue——flanked by the majestic statues of the Four Heavenly Kings, with a standing statue of Skanda Bodhisattva at the back, guarding the temple''s Dharma lineage. A horizontal plaque reading "All Delighted" hangs behind Maitreya, implying a smiling face and a mind free of cares. The danchi (vermilion platform) in front of the hall is spacious, with the Bell Tower and Drum Tower on both sides——the morning bell and evening drum resound throughout the temple from this center. The hall retains the architectural style of official Ming Dynasty buildings, with wooden structures left unpainted to show their natural color, reflecting the aesthetic pursuit of "simple elegance and solemnity" in Jiangnan Buddhist architecture.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_faxi_temple_sa_02.png'),
  ('法喜寺', 2, 'Yuantong Treasure Hall (Yuantong Baodian)', '圆通宝殿', '<p>The Yuantong Treasure Hall is the main hall of Faxisi, located at the core position of the temple''s central axis, with a floor area of about 500 square meters——the largest and highest-specification hall in the temple. The hall spans seven bays in width and five bays in depth, with a double-eave xieshan roof covered with yellow glazed tiles. The roof ridge is decorated with Buddhist auspicious patterns such as the bottle gourd and Dharma wheel, presenting a majestic and spectacular sight. Enshrined in the center of the hall is the gilded seated statue of the Thousand-Armed and Thousand-Eyed Guanyin Bodhisattva, about 5 meters in height, carved from camphor wood and fully gilded. The thousand hands each hold a Dharma instrument, and the thousand eyes compassionately regard all sentient beings——exquisite craftsmanship and solemnly sublime. On both sides of Guanyin are enshrined the two great Bodhisattvas Manjusri and Samantabhadra, while the back features a group sculpture of Guanyin on the Island, reappearing the grand scene of Guanyin preaching and liberating sentient beings on Mount Potalaka. The Yuantong Treasure Hall is where the incense burns most vigorously in Faxisi. Two ancient ginkgo trees in front of the hall are over 400 years old; when their golden leaves fall and cover the danchi in autumn, the scenery is absolutely stunning.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_faxi_temple_sa_03.png'),
  ('法喜寺', 3, 'Mahavira Hall (Daxiong Baodian)', '大雄宝殿', '<p>The Mahavira Hall is located behind the Yuantong Treasure Hall and is the highest-grade and most strictly regulated hall in Faxisi, as well as the core venue for large-scale Dharma assemblies, morning and evening chanting, and important Buddhist ritual activities. The hall spans seven bays in width and six bays in depth, with a double-eave hipped roof——the highest grade of ancient Chinese building roof form——covered with yellow glazed tiles. The main ridge is decorated with Two Dragons Playing with a Pearl, and the four sloping ridges each have immortal and beast statues, representing extremely high building specifications. Enshrined in the center of the hall are the Three Buddhas of the Horizontal Configuration: Sakyamuni Buddha in the center, Bhaisajyaguru (Medicine Buddha) in the east, and Amitabha Buddha in the west, each about 6 meters in height, fully gilded with solemn and majestic appearances. Behind the Buddha statues is a large group sculpture of Guanyin on the Island, while the side walls are painted with frescoes of the Twenty Devas, gorgeous in color and exquisite in brushwork. A spacious stone danchi is set in front of the Mahavira Hall, with sutra pillars, incense burners, and a life-release pool on both sides.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_faxi_temple_sa_04.png'),
  ('法喜寺', 4, 'Scripture Library (Cangjing Lou)', '藏经楼', '<p>The Scripture Library is located at the northernmost end of Faxisi''s central axis, behind the Mahavira Hall. It is the hall specifically used for collecting and enshrining the Buddhist Tripitaka and precious Buddhist scriptures, as well as an important venue for the abbot to preach the Dharma and for monastics to study scriptures in daily practice. The library is a two-story building with five bays in width and four bays in depth, featuring a double-eave ying-shan roof with green tiles and white walls, presenting an elegant and dignified style that follows the same tradition as Jiangnan''s traditional library architecture. Enshrined in the center of the first floor is a large reclining jade Buddha from Myanmar, over 6 meters in length——the largest jade Buddha statue in the temple. The jade quality is warm and smooth, with a compassionate appearance; many devotees offer incense and prostrate here. The second floor is the scripture collection area, housing precious Tripitaka versions such as the "Qianlong Tripitaka," "Yongle Northern Tripitaka," and "Fangshan Stone Scriptures," as well as handwritten manuscripts of treatises by eminent monks across dynasties. The courtyard in front of the Scripture Library is quiet and serene, planted with osmanthus, camellia, and slender bamboos——fragrant in all seasons.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_faxi_temple_sa_05.png'),
  ('法喜寺', 5, 'Hall of Ksitigarbha (Dizang Dian)', '地藏殿', '<p>The Hall of Ksitigarbha is located in the eastern side hall of Faxisi and is the hall dedicated to Ksitigarbha Bodhisattva. Ksitigarbha is one of the Four Great Bodhisattvas in Buddhism, deeply revered for his magnificient vow: "Until the hells are emptied, I will not become a Buddha." Enshrined in the center of the hall is the seated statue of Ksitigarbha Bodhisattva, about 3 meters in height, wearing a kasaya, holding a mani pearl and a khakkhara (monastic staff), with a compassionate and serene countenance. On both sides of the Ksitigarbha Hall are frescoes of the Ten Kings of Hell and illustrations of the Ten Kings of the Underworld, presenting the Buddhist concepts of karma and rebirth in graphic and textual form, warning the world to abstain from all evils and practice all virtues. The hall sees continuous incense offerings year-round, especially from devotees seeking to perform rites for deceased relatives or pray for blessings and disaster removal. The temple also regularly holds Buddhist rites such as Mengshan Almsgiving and Yankou (Hungry Ghost Festival rite) here. The Ksitigarbha Hall building features a single-eave ying-shan roof with green tiles and white walls.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_faxi_temple_sa_06.png'),
  ('法喜寺', 6, 'Hall of Five Hundred Arhats (Wubai Luohan Tang)', '五百罗汉堂', '<p>The Hall of Five Hundred Arhats is located in the western side hall of Faxisi and is the dedicated hall for enshrining the Five Hundred Arhats, also one of the larger and better-preserved Arhat Halls among Hangzhou temples. The Arhat Hall spans seven bays in width and three bays in depth, with a single-eave hipped roof, green tiles, and vermilion pillars——dignified yet elegant in architectural style. Inside the hall, shrines for the Five Hundred Arhats are arranged along three walls, each Arhat statue about 0.8 meters in height, round-carved from camphor wood and fully gilded. The Arhats have diverse expressions and are vividly lifelike—some with kind brows and benevolent eyes, some with glaring eyes, some holding sutra scrolls, some grasping Dharma instruments——no two are alike, fully demonstrating the superb level of ancient sculpture art. In the center of the hall are enshrined Vairocana Buddha and the two Bodhisattvas Manjusri and Samantabhadra, forming the "Three Saints of the Huayan" configuration. The four walls of the Arhat Hall are also painted with Buddhist story frescoes.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_faxi_temple_sa_07.png'),
  ('法喜寺', 7, 'White Cloud Peak Viewing Platform (Baiyunfeng Guanjing Tai)', '白云峰观景台', '<p>The White Cloud Peak Viewing Platform is located on White Cloud Peak behind Faxisi, at an altitude of about 280 meters, and is the viewing location with the most open视野 in the Faxisi scenic area. From behind the Scripture Library within the temple, follow the stone-step mountain path winding upward——it takes about 20-30 minutes to reach the peak viewing platform. The viewing platform is an open stone platform with cement faux-wood railings on all sides. Standing on the platform, you can take in the entire view of Hangzhou city——nearby are the layered mountains of the West Lake scenic area, with Middle and Lower Tianzhu Temples faintly visible among the green trees in the mountain col; in the distance, you can overlook the Qiantang River like a ribbon and the forest of high-rise buildings in the city. When the weather is clear, you can even see Xianghu Lake and the Binjiang New City in the distance. The mountain peak where the viewing platform is located also preserves the White Cloud Peak cliff engraving group, among which the most famous is the three large-character cliff engraving "White Cloud Peak" from the Ming Dynasty. Every morning, the peak is surrounded by swirling clouds and radiant sunrise glow.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_faxi_temple_sa_08.png'),
  ('法喜寺', 8, 'Imperial Stele Pavilion (Yubei Ting)', '御碑亭', '<p>The Imperial Stele Pavilion is located on the east side of the skywell between the Hall of Heavenly Kings and the Yuantong Treasure Hall, south of the Yuantong Treasure Hall within Faxisi. It is a Jiangnan classical pavilion building with a double-eave four-cornered pyramidal roof. Inside the pavilion stands an imperial stele personally inscribed by Emperor Qianlong of the Qing Dynasty during his southern inspections to Faxisi (then called "Shangtianzhu Preaching Temple"). The stele is about 2.5 meters high and 1 meter wide, with the stele top carved with coiling dragon motifs. The front of the stele body is engraved with two poems titled "Shangtianzhu" in Emperor Qianlong''s own calligraphy, while the back is engraved with poems harmonized by accompanying ministers——all in regular script, with vigorous brushwork and exquisite engraving craftsmanship. Emperor Qianlong visited the south six times and personally came to Shangtianzhu to pay respects to the Buddha on five occasions, speaking highly of Faxisi. The Imperial Stele Pavilion building is small, exquisite, and equipped with stone seating on all sides. Two century-old osmanthus trees are planted in front of the pavilion.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_faxi_temple_sa_09.png'),
  ('法喜寺', 9, 'Faxisi Vegetarian Dining Hall (Suzhai Tang)', '法喜寺素斋堂', '<p>The Faxisi Vegetarian Dining Hall is located on the west side of the temple, next to the Hall of Five Hundred Arhats. It is one of the most famous temple vegetarian dining halls in Hangzhou, attracting a large number of tourists and citizens who make special trips to taste its offerings every day. The vegetarian dining hall is an open hall that can accommodate about 200 people dining simultaneously. The interior decoration is dignified and elegantly simple, with no meat, fish, or alcohol served, fully embodying the pure spirit of Buddhist dietary culture. The varieties of vegetarian food are rich and diverse, including classic Hangzhou-style vegetarian dishes such as casual vegetarian noodles (about 15-20 RMB/bowl), vegetarian buns (3 RMB/each), vegetarian "roast goose" (made from tofu skin and mushrooms), and Luohan Vegetable (mixed vegetables with tofu and mushrooms). There are also elaborately crafted vegetarian set meals (about 50-80 RMB/set) and exquisite Buddhist vegetarian banquets. The ingredients mainly consist of fresh seasonal vegetables, tofu, mushrooms, and the temple''s own vegetable oil, emphasizing "Suzhou flavor, Hangzhou technique." The most famous is Faxisi''s vegetarian "roast goose," with crispy skin and fresh, fragrant filling——daily sales exceed a thousand portions. The dining hall also provides "Blessing Vegetarian Meals," where diners can offer incense and pray before meals.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_faxi_temple_sa_10.png'),
  ('大运河拱宸桥', 0, 'Yunhe Square (Canal Plaza)', '运河广场', '<p>Yunhe Square is located on the west bank of Gongchen Bridge in Gongshu District, at the southern terminus of the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal. It is an open urban square that showcases Hangzhou''s canal culture most comprehensively. The square is paved with bluestone slabs and antique-style floor tiles, with a large sailing ship sculpture standing at its center, symbolizing the millennial canal shipping culture. The east side of the square is adjacent to Gongchen Bridge, with waterfront steps and antique-style street lamps along the bank, making it a popular spot for citizens to take evening strolls, square dancing, and enjoying the canal night view. During holidays, the square hosts canal culture markets, intangible cultural heritage exhibitions, and light shows, bustling with activity. The surrounding area is equipped with tea culture houses, canal-themed restaurants, and cultural creative shops, where visitors can rest and enjoy tea while experiencing Hangzhou''s historical heritage of "prospering because of the canal." This is also one of the main boarding and disembarkation points for canal cruise boats on the Hangzhou section of the Grand Canal.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_gongchen_bridge_sa_01.png'),
  ('大运河拱宸桥', 1, 'Gongchen Bridge', '拱宸桥', '<p>Gongchen Bridge was first built in 1631 during the Ming Dynasty and stands as the southern terminus landmark of the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal. It is the longest, highest, and widest surviving stone arch bridge in Hangzhou. The bridge spans 98 meters with a height of 16 meters, featuring a three-arch thin-pier structure. The deck is paved with long bluestone slabs, flanked by stone balustrades and pillar posts carved with lotus motifs in an antique and majestic style. The name "Gongchen" derives from the phrase "gongweichenji," meaning to guard the imperial seat with reverence, symbolizing respect for the emperor. Historically, Gongchen Bridge marked the terminal point where canal shipping boats arrived in Hangzhou, and merchants from all over would dock and disembark here, gradually forming a bustling market on the west side of the bridge, creating the magnificent scene of "Ten Li of Silver Hushu." Today, Gongchen Bridge remains vibrant with traffic and pedestrians. The ancient bridge stretches across the sparkling canal waters, with the Qiaoxi Historical and Cultural Block on the west bank and the commercial district on the east bank. At dusk, the setting sun casts its glow on the ancient stone railings while canal boats glide slowly by—a truly moving scene.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_gongchen_bridge_sa_02.png'),
  ('大运河拱宸桥', 2, 'Qiaoxi Historical and Cultural Block', '桥西历史文化街区', '<p>The Qiaoxi Historical and Cultural Block is located on the west bank of Gongchen Bridge and is one of the best-preserved historical blocks along the Hangzhou section of the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal. Covering an area of about 7.8 hectares, the block retains a large number of residential houses, workshops, shops, and dock ruins from the late Qing Dynasty and early Republican era, fully presenting the historical features of canal handicraft civilization. Strolling through the block, visitors see bluestone roads flanked by restored black-tiled and white-walled buildings. Along the street are time-honored shops such as Zhang Xiaoquan, Wang Xingji, and West Lake Silk Umbrella, as well as numerous independent cafes, cultural creative studios, and handicraft workshops. The block houses four national-level thematic museums: China Umbrella Museum, China Knife, Scissors and Sword Museum, China Fan Museum, and Hangzhou Arts and Crafts Museum. The block connects with Xiaohe Straight Street to the south and extends north to the Grand Canal Traditional Chinese Medicine Hall and Zhang Daxian Temple, with a total length of about 1.5 kilometers.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_gongchen_bridge_sa_03.png'),
  ('大运河拱宸桥', 3, 'China Umbrella Museum', '中国伞博物馆', '<p>The China Umbrella Museum is located within the Qiaoxi Historical and Cultural Block and officially opened to the public in 2009. It is the only thematic museum in the world dedicated to umbrellas. With a floor area of about 5,000 square meters and the theme "Umbrellas Across the World," the museum systematically showcases the evolution of Chinese umbrella craftsmanship and the rich imagery of umbrellas in literature, art, and folklore through four major exhibition sections. The museum displays over a thousand umbrella artifacts from the Warring States period to the present, including exquisite West Lake silk umbrellas, Dong ethnic Baijia umbrellas, Yi ethnic Chao''erwa rain capes, and modern automatic umbrellas. Among these, the West Lake silk umbrella—with Hangzhou specialty silk as the surface and bamboo as the frame—is renowned for its gorgeous colors and exquisite craftsmanship, representing one of Hangzhou''s most iconic intangible cultural heritage crafts. The museum employs multimedia interactive technologies, allowing visitors to experience the oil-paper umbrella painting process firsthand.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_gongchen_bridge_sa_04.png'),
  ('大运河拱宸桥', 4, 'China Knife, Scissors and Sword Museum', '中国刀剪剑博物馆', '<p>The China Knife, Scissors and Sword Museum is adjacent to the China Umbrella Museum and is part of the Qiaoxi Museum Cluster, officially opened to the public in 2009. With four core thematic exhibition halls——"The Spirit of Knives, Scissors and Swords," "Knives and Our Lives," "The Story of Scissors," and "Sword: From Weapon to Ritual Vessel"—the museum systematically traces the evolutionary trajectory of knives, scissors, and swords throughout Chinese history. The museum collection includes over 2,000 precious artifacts and time-honored brand masterpieces, ranging from Neolithic stone knives and Shang-Zhou bronze swords to Han Dynasty ring-pommel knives, Tang Dynasty hengdao swords, Ming-Qing Longquan swords, and modern Zhang Xiaoquan scissors and Wang Mazi knives. Many of these are classified as national-level cultural relics. The museum places special emphasis on interactive experiences, with immersive zones such as "Forging a Pair of Scissors" and "Sword-Casting Workshop," where visitors can try their hand at forging and blade-grinding under the guidance of professional craftsmen. The museum building itself was converted from an old factory workshop, retaining the rugged aesthetics of industrial heritage.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_gongchen_bridge_sa_05.png'),
  ('大运河拱宸桥', 5, 'China Fan Museum', '中国扇博物馆', '<p>The China Fan Museum is located within the Qiaoxi Historical and Cultural Block, adjacent to the China Umbrella Museum and China Knife, Scissors and Sword Museum, together forming a unique museum cluster in Hangzhou. The museum was completed and opened in 2009, with a floor area of about 2,000 square meters. With the theme "Chinese Fan Culture," it features three permanent exhibition halls—"Chinese Fan History," "Chinese Fan Art," and "Chinese Fan Folklore"—systematically showcasing the evolutionary journey of fans from ritual objects and cooling tools to artistic treasures. The museum houses over a thousand precious artifacts ranging from fan surface fragments in Warring States silk paintings, Tang-Song round fans, Ming-Qing folding fans, to modern Wang Xingji exquisite fans. Among these, the Southern Song "Silk Round Fan" and the Qing Dynasty "Ivory-bone Fine-colored Painting Folding Fan" are the museum''s crown jewels. The museum specially sets up a "Fan Surface Painting Interactive Zone," where visitors can experience fan surface calligraphy and painting creation under professional guidance, appreciating the elegant lifestyle of Chinese literati. The Wang Xingji Fan Studio, founded in 1875, has its fan-making craft listed as a National Intangible Cultural Heritage. The museum has a dedicated "Wang Xingji Fan Art Zone" that completely presents the fan-making craftsmanship of this century-old brand.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_gongchen_bridge_sa_06.png'),
  ('大运河拱宸桥', 6, 'Hangzhou Arts and Crafts Museum', '杭州工艺美术博物馆', '<p>The Hangzhou Arts and Crafts Museum is located at the southern end of the Qiaoxi Historical and Cultural Block, converted from the old factory building of the former Hangzhou Honglei Silk Weaving Factory, and officially opened to the public in 2009. With a floor area of about 7,000 square meters and the theme "Hangzhou Arts and Crafts," the museum features six permanent exhibition halls that systematically showcase the development of Hangzhou''s arts and crafts since the Neolithic Age. The museum houses over 3,000 exquisite arts and crafts pieces, including Du Jinsheng brocade, Southern Song Guan kiln porcelain, Wang Xingji fans, Zhang Xiaoquan scissors, West Lake silk umbrellas, and bamboo weaving crafts, many of which are representative works by national-level master craftsmen. The museum places special emphasis on living inheritance, with "Master Craftsman Studios" set up year-round where visitors can observe the entire creative process of masters on-site and have the opportunity to try their hand at intangible cultural heritage experience projects such as embroidery, bamboo weaving, and folding fan painting. The museum building retains the industrial charm of the original factory building.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_gongchen_bridge_sa_07.png'),
  ('大运河拱宸桥', 7, 'Zhang Daxian Temple', '张大仙庙', '<p>Zhang Daxian Temple is located at the north end of the Qiaoxi Historical Block, next to the Grand Canal Traditional Chinese Medicine Hall. It is a small folk temple dedicated to Zhang Daxian, a Taoist priest from the Southern Song Dynasty. Zhang Daxian, originally named Zhang Qizhen, lived in seclusion in Hangzhou during the Southern Song period and was renowned among local communities for his exceptional medical skills and benevolent nature. After his death, he was revered by the people as "Zhang Daxian," and the temple has been maintained for over 700 years. The temple is modest in scale with only one courtyard, but features black tiles, white walls, and upturned eaves—a typical Jiangnan folk temple style. The main hall enshrines a statue of Zhang Daxian, with renowned physicians enshrined on both sides, reflecting the folk belief characteristic of "integrating medicine and Taoism" in Hangzhou. On the small square in front of the temple, stone tables and benches are set up where neighboring residents often play chess, chat, and bask in the sun, full of everyday community life. Every year on the third day of the third lunar month, the temple fair is held.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_gongchen_bridge_sa_08.png'),
  ('大运河拱宸桥', 8, 'Xiaohe Park', '小河公园', '<p>Xiaohe Park is located south of Xiaohe Straight Street in Gongshu District, along the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal. It was converted from the former Hangzhou Xiaohe Oil Depot site and officially opened to the public in 2022, serving as an important node of the Hangzhou Grand Canal National Cultural Park. Covering an area of about 5.6 hectares, the park ingeniously preserves the industrial relics of the original oil depot, including four large oil tanks, a loading and unloading dock, and oil pipelines, which are connected as a whole through steel structure corridors, landscape walkways, and green vegetation. The four giant oil tanks have been transformed into immersive light and shadow art spaces, presenting brilliant visual effects under built-in lighting at night, making it a new popular打卡 spot in Hangzhou. Along the canal side, the park features a waterfront walkway about 10 meters wide, flanked by weeping willows, camphor trees, and cherry blossoms, offering diverse scenery throughout the four seasons. Xiaohe Park''s renovation concept embodies Hangzhou''s urban renewal approach of "revitalizing industrial heritage through adaptive reuse" and stands as a model project in the construction of the canal cultural belt.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_gongchen_bridge_sa_09.png'),
  ('大运河拱宸桥', 9, 'Fuyi Granary', '富义仓', '<p>Fuyi Granary is located at the southern section of the Hangzhou segment of the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal, within Xiawan Lane. It was first built in 1880 during the Qing Dynasty and served as an important granary site in the canal shipping system, hailed alongside Beijing''s Nanxincang as the "Twin Gems of Granaries Under Heaven." The granary covers an area of about 8,000 square meters, originally consisting of four rows and five sections totaling sixty rooms. The existing building complex is currently the only well-preserved Qing Dynasty granary architectural cluster in Hangzhou. The entire complex adopts a traditional courtyard-style layout with black-tiled hard-mountain roofs, thick walls, and small windows, incorporating functions of thermal insulation, moisture prevention, and theft protection, reflecting the wisdom of ancient granary architecture. In 2007, Fuyi Granary completed protective renovation and was transformed into a canal culture exhibition center and cultural creative space. The interior houses a permanent exhibition themed "The Canal and Hangzhou," narrating the close relationship between the Grand Canal and Hangzhou''s urban development through texts, images, artifacts, and multimedia. Fuyi Granary is one of the heritage sites for the Grand Canal''s application for UNESCO World Heritage status.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_gongchen_bridge_sa_10.png'),
  ('河坊街（清河坊历史街区）', 0, 'Hefang Street East Entrance (Dongrukou)', '河坊街东入口', '<p>The East Entrance of Hefang Street is located at the intersection of Zhongshan Middle Road and Hefang Street in Shangcheng District, Hangzhou. It is the eastern starting point of the Hefang Street pedestrian zone. The entrance is paved with neat bluestone slabs, and both sides of the street feature restored architectural complexes in Ming-Qing style, with black tiles, white walls, and carved wood windows——the rich ancient atmosphere greets visitors instantly. Nearby the entrance are various Hangzhou time-honored brand shops, including Wang Xingji Fan Studio, Zhang Xiaoquan Scissors, and Hu Qingyutang Traditional Chinese Medicine, among others. Once visitors step in from this entrance, they formally enter the core area of Hangzhou''s millennial civilian culture. Hefang Street has a total length of about 1,800 meters, of which the Qinghefang section (from the East Entrance to Nanshan Road) is a pedestrian street——one of the most completely preserved and representative historical and cultural blocks in Hangzhou. Every weekend and holiday, the area in front of the East Entrance teems with crowds.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_hefang_street_sa_01.png'),
  ('河坊街（清河坊历史街区）', 1, 'Drum Tower (Gulou)', '鼓楼', '<p>The Drum Tower is located at the east end of Hefang Street, at the intersection of Zhongshan Middle Road and Wangjiang Road. It is an important historical and cultural site and landmark building in Hangzhou. The Drum Tower was first built during the Five Dynasties period in the Wuyue Kingdom (approx. 907 CE) and originally served as the south gate of Lin''an City''s inner citadel——Chaotian Gate——in the Southern Song Dynasty, being the south gate of ancient Hangzhou and holding a prominent status. Historically, the Drum Tower was destroyed by war and fire multiple times and rebuilt repeatedly. The existing building was reconstructed in 2002 according to the Ming Dynasty Drum Tower form. The Drum Tower is a three-story wooden tower-style building with a double-eave xieshan roof, red walls, and black tiles, about 20 meters in height, presenting a majestic bearing. The first floor houses the "Southern Song Lin''an City Historical Relics Exhibition," recreating the prosperous scene of Lin''an, the Southern Song capital, through texts, models, and multimedia. The second floor is a tea culture exhibition space where visitors can taste tea and rest.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_hefang_street_sa_02.png'),
  ('河坊街（清河坊历史街区）', 2, 'Wangxian Pavilion (Wangxiange)', '望仙阁', '<p>Wangxian Pavilion is located in the middle section of Hefang Street, adjacent to the Southern Song Imperial Street ruins. It is a three-story tower-style building in Ming-Qing style and the best high vantage point within Hefang Street for viewing the surroundings. The pavilion''s name originates from a touching Southern Song legend: when Emperor Gaozong of Song (Zhao Gou) crossed south and stationed in Hangzhou, he once gazed into the distance from this spot and suddenly saw immortal figures appearing in auspicious clouds. A pavilion was subsequently built to commemorate this event, hence the name "Wangxian" (Gazing at Immortals) Pavilion. The pavilion is about 16 meters high, with a double-eave pyramidal roof, vermilion pillars, and surrounding corridors——elegant and exquisite in architectural style. The first floor houses a Hangzhou old photographs exhibition, displaying precious old photos of Hangzhou''s city walls, streets, and canal from the late Qing and early Republican period. The second floor is a Southern Song culture exhibition space. The third floor is an open viewing terrace. Wangxian Pavilion is also one of the best photography spots on Hefang Street.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_hefang_street_sa_03.png'),
  ('河坊街（清河坊历史街区）', 3, 'Hu Qingyutang Traditional Chinese Medicine Museum', '胡庆余堂中药博物馆', '<p>The Hu Qingyutang Traditional Chinese Medicine Museum is located within Da Jing Lane on Hefang Street and was converted from the original site of the Hu Qingyutang pharmaceutical workshop. It officially opened to the public in 1989 and is the only national-level traditional Chinese medicine specialized museum in China. Hu Qingyutang was founded in 1874 by Hu Xueyan, a renowned Anhui merchant in the late Qing Dynasty, and is hailed as the "Jiangnan Medicine King," standing alongside Beijing Tongrentang as the "Two Great Pharmacies of North and South." The museum covers an area of about 3,000 square meters and completely preserves the "front shop, back workshop" architectural layout of the Qing Dynasty pharmacy——the front hall serving as the sales and exhibition area, and the back hall as the pharmaceutical workshop and medicinal material storage area. The museum houses over ten thousand pieces of traditional Chinese medicinal material specimens, pharmaceutical tools, and precious medical books. Visitors can closely observe pharmaceutical workers demonstrating traditional Chinese medicine production processes such as slicing herbs, grinding powder, and making pills on-site.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_hefang_street_sa_04.png'),
  ('河坊街（清河坊历史街区）', 4, 'Fang Huichun Tang (Fang Huichuntang)', '方回春堂', '<p>Fang Huichun Tang is located at 117 Hefang Street and was founded in 1649 (the sixth year of the Shunzhi reign of the Qing Dynasty) by the Fang family of Qiantang. It is the oldest surviving traditional Chinese medicine time-honored brand in Hangzhou, predating Hu Qingyutang by 225 years. The name "Huichun" (Returning Spring) is derived from the meaning of "rejuvenating the elderly and restoring health with miraculous skills," and the hall has long been renowned for its "authentic medicinal materials, meticulous processing, and renowned physicians practicing on-site." The medicine hall is a late Qing residential building with three courtyards and two skywells, featuring black tiles, white walls, and carved gate towers, preserving the complete layout of ancient TCM halls. Currently, Fang Huichun Tang offers comprehensive TCM diagnosis and treatment services including internal medicine, gynecology, pediatrics, and acupuncture and tuina massage, with over ten renowned veteran TCM doctors stationed there. The hall also regularly holds public welfare activities such as "National TCM Day," "Herbal Paste Festival," and "Parent-Child Paste Experience." During the winter paste festival period, free clinic services and constitution identification are also provided.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_hefang_street_sa_05.png'),
  ('河坊街（清河坊历史街区）', 5, 'Zhu Bingren Copper Sculpture Art Museum (Jiangnan Copper House)', '朱炳仁铜雕艺术博物馆（江南铜屋）', '<p>The Zhu Bingren Copper Sculpture Art Museum is also known as the "Jiangnan Copper House" and is located at 207 Hefang Street. It was founded in 2007 by Mr. Zhu Bingren, a national-level arts and crafts master and the fourth-generation inheritor of "Zhu Family Copper Art." It is the only thematic museum in China dedicated to copper sculpture art. The entire museum building is constructed with copper walls, copper roof, and copper pillars——from the roof and walls to the floor and doors/windows——consuming about 150 tons of pure copper in total, presenting a magnificent and spectacular sight, hailed as an "epic written in copper." The museum is divided into four major exhibition sections: "Copper History Corridor," "Zhu Bingren Copper Sculpture Masterpieces Exhibition," "Copper and Life," and "Copper Architecture Art," displaying over a thousand exquisite works by Zhu Bingren and three generations of copper art inheritors from his family. Among these, the 5-meter-high purple copper "Leifeng Pagoda" model, the 3-ton "Copper Bridge," and the "Copper Calligraphy" series are all crown jewels of the museum. The museum also has a copper sculpture interactive experience zone.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_hefang_street_sa_06.png'),
  ('河坊街（清河坊历史街区）', 6, 'Jiangnan Copper House (Jiangnan Tongwu)', '江南铜屋', '<p>The Jiangnan Copper House is the alternative name for the Zhu Bingren Copper Sculpture Art Museum and also the most stunning core landscape of the museum. The entire building is strictly constructed according to the "front hall, back main hall, with side wings" layout of Ming-Qing Jiangnan residential buildings, with three courtyards, two skywells, and a column-and-tie wooden (copper) structure. Everything from the exterior to the interior decorations is made of copper——the doors and windows are copper, the pillars are copper, the handrails are copper, and even the floor paving and ceiling decorations are copper, totaling over 150 tons of pure copper consumed, with a cost of tens of millions of yuan. The Copper House appears with "black tiles" (copper tiles) and "white walls" (copper walls), with upturned eaves and carved beams——under sunlight it glitters with golden light, presenting a magnificent sight. Inside the copper house, thematic exhibition areas such as "Copper Study," "Copper Tea Room," "Copper Buddha Hall," and "Copper Garden" are set up. The Copper House itself is also a rare giant copper sculpture artwork.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_hefang_street_sa_07.png'),
  ('河坊街（清河坊历史街区）', 7, 'Southern Song Imperial Street (NanSong Yujie)', '南宋御街', '<p>The Southern Song Imperial Street is located on Zhongshan Middle Road in Shangcheng District, Hangzhou, extending from the Drum Tower in the south to Zhongbei Bridge in the north, with a total length of about 4,000 meters. It was the central axis of Lin''an City (the Southern Song capital) and the exclusive ancient road where emperors passed on their way to offer sacrifices to heaven at the Jingling Palace. The Imperial Road ruins were discovered in 2008 at the Yangguan Lane section of Zhongshan Middle Road. Subsequently, Hangzhou launched the comprehensive conservation project for the Imperial Street, transforming the areas along the street into an open pedestrian block according to the principle of "restoring the old to its original form." Today''s Southern Song Imperial Street retains bluestone slab pavement and underground imperial road ruin display windows——visitors can view the crushed stone cushion layer, drainage ditches, and floor tile ruins of the Southern Song Imperial Road through specially-made glass flooring. The Southern Song Imperial Street and Hefang Street intersect in a cross pattern, together forming the "Qinghefang-Southern Song Imperial Street" historical and cultural block.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_hefang_street_sa_08.png'),
  ('河坊街（清河坊历史街区）', 8, 'Dajing Lane (Dajing Xiang)', '大井巷', '<p>Dajing Lane is located on the south side of Hefang Street, at the foot of Wu Mountain. It connects Zhongshan South Road on the east and links to Hefang Street on the west. It is a quiet historical lane about 300 meters long. The lane''s name originates from a five-eye ancient well——Dajing (Big Well)——built during the Five Dynasties period in the Wuyue Kingdom, inside the lane. The well mouth has five water drawing holes, allowing five households to draw water simultaneously. It was one of the important public water sources in ancient Hangzhou, and nearby residents still draw water for drinking from it to this day. Both sides of the lane retain a large number of Hangzhou-style residential houses from the late Qing and early Republican period, with black tiles, white walls, wooden doors, and stone steps. Dajing Lane is also one of the convenient paths to the Wu Mountain scenic area and Chenghuang Pavilion. Because the lane is relatively narrow and has not undergone excessive commercial development, it is one of the few "living old Hangzhou" blocks in the vicinity of Hefang Street.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_hefang_street_sa_09.png'),
  ('河坊街（清河坊历史街区）', 9, 'Wushan Square and Chenghuang Pavilion (Wushan Guangchang yu Chenghuang Ge)', '吴山广场与城隍阁', '<p>Wushan Square is located at the foot of Wushan Hill, on the south side of Hefang Street in Shangcheng District, Hangzhou. It is a landmark open urban square at the southern end of old Hangzhou''s urban area and a comprehensive public space for citizens'' fitness, leisure, and large-scale events. The square covers an area of about 5 hectares, paved with granite floor tiles, with a large musical fountain and a sunken performance stage in the center. Every weekend and holiday, intangible cultural heritage markets, folk performance exhibitions, and open-air concerts are held here. From the southern end of the square, follow the stone-step mountain path winding upward——it takes about 20-30 minutes to reach the summit of Wushan, where the landmark Chenghuang Pavilion stands. Chenghuang Pavilion is a seven-story antique-style building, about 40 meters high, with upturned eaves and vermilion walls. Ascending the pavilion offers a 360-degree overlook of Hangzhou''s cityscape. Wushan itself is also an important cultural famous mountain in Hangzhou, with many scenic spots such as the "Twelve Zodiac Rocks," "River and Lake Convergence Viewing Pavilion," and "Medicine King Temple" on the mountain.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_hefang_street_sa_10.png'),
  ('京杭大运河（杭州段）', 0, 'Wulinmen Dock (Wulinmen Matou)', '武林门码头', '<p>Wulinmen Dock is located on the north side of Wulin Square in Gongshu District, Hangzhou, on the bank of the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal. It is the largest cruise ship dock with the most complete facilities on the Hangzhou section of the canal, and also the main departure station for Hangzhou water buses and canal sightseeing cruise ships. The dock is equipped with a modern passenger waiting hall, complete with air conditioning, seating, electronic display screens, and ticket windows, dispatching over a million passengers annually. Departing from Wulinmen Dock, visitors can take the water bus (about 3 RMB/stop) southward along the canal, passing scenic spots such as Xinyi Square, Fuyi Granary, and Gongchen Bridge, covering a total distance of about 12 kilometers——hailed as the "Oriental Venice" water bus line. During traditional festivals such as Dragon Boat Festival and Mid-Autumn Festival, the dock also hosts folk activities such as "Canal Dragon Boat Race" and "Canal Moon Appreciation," bustling with excitement.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_grand_canal_sa_01.png'),
  ('京杭大运河（杭州段）', 1, 'West Lake Cultural Square (Xihu Wenhua Guangchang)', '西湖文化广场', '<p>West Lake Cultural Square is located in Gongshu District, Hangzhou, facing Wulin Square across the river at the southernmost end of the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal section in Hangzhou. It is one of Hangzhou''s most important urban cultural squares. The square covers an area of about 13.3 hectares and consists of four parts: the main square, musical fountain, canal landscape belt, and cultural venue cluster. Standing at the center of the square is the Global Center, about 100 meters high (one of Hangzhou''s supertall buildings). To the north are arranged in order the three major provincial-level cultural venues: Zhejiang Provincial Museum, Zhejiang Museum of Natural History, and Zhejiang Science and Technology Museum, making it the area with the densest cultural facilities in Hangzhou. The main fountain of the square is one of Hangzhou''s largest musical fountains, operating on a regular schedule daily with coordinated lighting and music, with water jets reaching up to 60 meters high——the night view is especially spectacular.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_grand_canal_sa_02.png'),
  ('京杭大运河（杭州段）', 2, 'Xinyi Square (Xinyifang)', '信义坊', '<p>Xinyi Square is located on the west bank of the northern section of the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal in Gongshu District, Hangzhou, south of Daguan Bridge. It is a waterfront cultural leisure block transformed from historical streets and lanes. The block relies on the old street and lane layout on the west bank of the canal, preserving a large number of residential buildings from the late Qing Dynasty and early Republican period, while introducing modern cultural creativity, dining, and leisure businesses, forming a unique character of "old Hangzhou negatives, new city living room." Xinyi Square Water Street is the main axis of the block, with a total length of about 500 meters, built along the canal. On one side are restored black-tiled and white-walled residential buildings, and on the other side is the open canal water surface, with occasional sculling boats gliding by——the scenery is full of Jiangnan watertown charm. The block regularly hosts cultural events such as "Canal Culture Market" and "Xinyi Square Music Festival." Compared to the bustling Qiaoxi Historical and Cultural Block, Xinyi Square appears more tranquil.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_grand_canal_sa_03.png'),
  ('京杭大运河（杭州段）', 3, 'Fuyi Granary (Fuyicang)', '富义仓', '<p>Fuyi Granary is located at the southern section of the Hangzhou segment of the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal, within Xiawan Lane. It was first built in 1880 during the Qing Dynasty and served as an important granary site in the canal shipping system, hailed alongside Beijing''s Nanxincang as the "Twin Gems of Granaries Under Heaven." The granary covers an area of about 8,000 square meters, originally consisting of four rows and five sections totaling sixty rooms. The existing building complex is currently the only well-preserved Qing Dynasty granary architectural cluster in Hangzhou. The entire complex adopts a traditional courtyard-style layout with black-tiled hard-mountain roofs, thick walls, and small windows, incorporating functions of thermal insulation, moisture prevention, and theft protection, reflecting the wisdom of ancient granary architecture. In 2007, Fuyi Granary completed protective renovation and was transformed into a canal culture exhibition center and cultural creative space. The interior houses a permanent exhibition themed "The Canal and Hangzhou," narrating the close relationship between the Grand Canal and Hangzhou''s urban development through texts, images, artifacts, and multimedia. Fuyi Granary is one of the heritage sites for the Grand Canal''s application for UNESCO World Heritage status.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_grand_canal_sa_04.png'),
  ('京杭大运河（杭州段）', 4, 'Xiaohe Straight Street (Xiaohe Zhijie)', '小河直街', '<p>Xiaohe Straight Street is located at the convergence of the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal and Xiaohe Creek in Gongshu District, Hangzhou. It is the main axis of the Xiaohe Historical and Cultural Block and one of the best-preserved historical blocks of canal civilian life in Hangzhou. The block was built along Xiaohe Creek, with a total length of about 500 meters. Both sides retain a large number of canal residential houses from the late Qing Dynasty and early Republican period——mostly in the layout of "front shop, back residence" or "lower shop, upper residence," with black tiles, white walls, wooden doors, and stone steps, authentically presenting the living conditions of canal-side common people a century ago. Unlike other overly commercialized historical blocks, Xiaohe Straight Street still has a large number of original residents living there. The block regularly hosts canal culture events and is an important node of the Hangzhou Canal Cultural Belt. Visitors can experience sculling boat rides, taste canal-side tea, listen to old Hangzhou residents tell stories, and feel the unique charm of a "living historical block."</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_grand_canal_sa_05.png'),
  ('京杭大运河（杭州段）', 5, 'Xiaohe Park (Xiaohe Gongyuan)', '小河公园', '<p>Xiaohe Park is located south of Xiaohe Straight Street in Gongshu District, along the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal. It was converted from the former Hangzhou Xiaohe Oil Depot site and officially opened to the public in 2022, serving as an important node of the Hangzhou Grand Canal National Cultural Park. Covering an area of about 5.6 hectares, the park ingeniously preserves the industrial relics of the original oil depot, including four large oil tanks, a loading and unloading dock, and oil pipelines, which are connected as a whole through steel structure corridors, landscape walkways, and green vegetation. The four giant oil tanks have been transformed into immersive light and shadow art spaces, presenting brilliant visual effects under built-in lighting at night, making it a new popular打卡 spot in Hangzhou. Along the canal side, the park features a waterfront walkway about 10 meters wide, flanked by weeping willows, camphor trees, and cherry blossoms, offering diverse scenery throughout the four seasons.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_grand_canal_sa_06.png'),
  ('京杭大运河（杭州段）', 6, 'Qiaoxi Historical and Cultural Block (Qiaoxi Lishi Wenhua Jiequ)', '桥西历史文化街区', '<p>The Qiaoxi Historical and Cultural Block is located on the west bank of Gongchen Bridge and is one of the best-preserved historical blocks along the Hangzhou section of the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal. Covering an area of about 7.8 hectares, the block retains a large number of residential houses, workshops, shops, and dock ruins from the late Qing Dynasty and early Republican era, fully presenting the historical features of canal handicraft civilization. Strolling through the block, visitors see bluestone roads flanked by restored black-tiled and white-walled buildings. Along the street are time-honored shops such as Zhang Xiaoquan, Wang Xingji, and West Lake Silk Umbrella, as well as numerous independent cafes, cultural creative studios, and handicraft workshops. The block houses four national-level thematic museums: China Umbrella Museum, China Knife, Scissors and Sword Museum, China Fan Museum, and Hangzhou Arts and Crafts Museum. The block connects with Xiaohe Straight Street to the south and extends north to the Grand Canal Traditional Chinese Medicine Hall and Zhang Daxian Temple, with a total length of about 1.5 kilometers.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_grand_canal_sa_07.png'),
  ('京杭大运河（杭州段）', 7, 'China Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal Museum (Zhongguo Jinghang Da Yunhe Bowuguan)', '中国京杭大运河博物馆', '<p>The China Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal Museum is located south of Canal Square in Gongshu District, Hangzhou, and officially opened to the public in 2006. It is the only national-level thematic museum in China dedicated to the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal. With a floor area of about 12,000 square meters and the theme "The Canal Changed China," the museum systematically showcases the long history of over 2,500 years from 486 BCE when King Fuchai of Wu excavated the Han Ditch to the present, as well as the profound impact of the Grand Canal on Chinese civilization in politics, economy, culture, and water conservancy. The museum houses over ten thousand pieces of cultural relics, ancient books, charts, and models related to the Grand Canal, including precious artifacts such as a Sui Dynasty gilt bronze door knocker, a Yuan Dynasty canal ship rudder, and a Ming Dynasty complete map of the canal. The museum building is shaped like a giant canal ship about to set sail, magnificent in bearing. The museum also regularly holds canal culture lectures, temporary special exhibitions, and youth research activities.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_grand_canal_sa_08.png'),
  ('京杭大运河（杭州段）', 8, 'Gongchen Bridge (Gongchen Qiao)', '拱宸桥', '<p>Gongchen Bridge was first built in 1631 during the Ming Dynasty and stands as the southern terminus landmark of the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal. It is the longest, highest, and widest surviving stone arch bridge in Hangzhou. The bridge spans 98 meters with a height of 16 meters, featuring a three-arch thin-pier structure. The deck is paved with long bluestone slabs, flanked by stone balustrades and pillar posts carved with lotus motifs in an antique and majestic style. The name "Gongchen" derives from the phrase "gongweichenji," meaning to guard the imperial seat with reverence, symbolizing respect for the emperor. Historically, Gongchen Bridge marked the terminal point where canal shipping boats arrived in Hangzhou, and merchants from all over would dock and disembark here, gradually forming a bustling market on the west side of the bridge, creating the magnificent scene of "Ten Li of Silver Hushu." Today, Gongchen Bridge remains vibrant with traffic and pedestrians. The ancient bridge stretches across the sparkling canal waters, with the Qiaoxi Historical and Cultural Block on the west bank and the commercial district on the east bank. At dusk, the setting sun casts its glow on the ancient stone railings while canal boats glide slowly by—a truly moving scene.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_grand_canal_sa_09.png'),
  ('京杭大运河（杭州段）', 9, 'Yunhe Square (Yunhe Guangchang)', '运河广场', '<p>Yunhe Square is located on the west bank of Gongchen Bridge in Gongshu District, at the southern terminus of the Beijing-Hangzhou Grand Canal. It is an open urban square that showcases Hangzhou''s canal culture most comprehensively. The square is paved with bluestone slabs and antique-style floor tiles, with a large sailing ship sculpture standing at its center, symbolizing the millennial canal shipping culture. The east side of the square is adjacent to Gongchen Bridge, with waterfront steps and antique-style street lamps along the bank, making it a popular spot for citizens to take evening strolls, square dancing and enjoying the canal night view. During holidays, the square hosts canal culture markets, intangible cultural heritage exhibitions, and light shows, bustling with activity. The surrounding area is equipped with tea culture houses, canal-themed restaurants, and cultural creative shops, where visitors can rest and enjoy tea while experiencing Hangzhou''s historical heritage of "prospering because of the canal." This is also one of the main boarding and disembarkation points for canal cruise boats on the Hangzhou section of the Grand Canal.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_grand_canal_sa_10.png'),
  ('雷峰塔', 0, 'Leifeng Pagoda Scenic Area Entrance (Leifeng Ta Jingqu Rukou)', '雷峰塔景区入口', '<p>The Leifeng Pagoda Scenic Area Entrance is located on the west side of Nanshan Road in Xihu District, Hangzhou, at the foot of Xizhao Mountain on the south shore of West Lake. It is the formal starting point for entering the Leifeng Pagoda Scenic Area and visiting Leifeng Pagoda. The entrance is paved with neat bluestone slab steps, with a gate house featuring a five-bay, double-eave xieshan roof antique-style building, complete with black tiles, vermilion pillars, and upturned eaves. A horizontal plaque inscribed with the three large characters "Leifeng Pagoda" hangs at the entrance, presenting a dignified bearing. The entrance square is equipped with a scenic area introduction stone tablet, tour guide map, and electronic ticket office, where visitors can purchase tickets (approx. 40 RMB/person), collect guide brochures, and plan their visit route. From the entrance to the foot of Leifeng Pagoda, it takes about 5-8 minutes of walking.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_leifeng_pagoda_sa_01.png'),
  ('雷峰塔', 1, 'Leifeng Pagoda Ruins Base (Leifeng Ta Yizhi Diceng)', '雷峰塔遗址底层', '<p>The Leifeng Pagoda Ruins Base is located at the bottom of the new Leifeng Pagoda and is the core space for the protective exhibition of the original pagoda ruins from the Five Dynasties period of the Wuyue Kingdom. The original Leifeng Pagoda was constructed under the supervision of King Qian Chu of Wuyue in 975 CE (eighth year of the Kaibao reign of Northern Song). On September 25, 1924, the millennial ancient pagoda collapsed with a loud crash due to excessive brick theft by the public, and the thousand-year-old pagoda was destroyed in an instant. In 2002, the new pagoda was reconstructed on the original site according to the concept of "pagoda covering ruins." The bottom of the new pagoda is completely elevated, and the original pagoda ruins are intactly preserved beneath the tempered glass flooring of the base level. Visitors can follow the circular walkway to view the complete appearance of the ruins from 360 degrees——the remaining brick pagoda body, pagoda foundation, auxiliary hall pillar bases, plinths, and underground palace excavation pit are all clearly visible.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_leifeng_pagoda_sa_02.png'),
  ('雷峰塔', 2, 'New Leifeng Pagoda First Floor (Xin Leifeng Ta Diyiceng)', '新雷峰塔一层', '<p>The first floor of the new Leifeng Pagoda is located above the ruins base level and serves as the base-level cultural exhibition space of the new pagoda. It is also the first floor that visitors see after entering the new pagoda. In the center of the first floor is a large Dongyang wood carving screen titled "Scene of Wuyue Building the Pagoda," about 4 meters high and 8 meters wide. In relief form, it completely recreates the grand scene of King Qian Chu supervising the construction of Leifeng Pagoda during the Five Dynasties Wuyue Kingdom period——from felling trees and quarrying stones, transporting materials, craftsmen''s construction, to the final completion. The four walls are hung with large meticulous-color frescoes titled "Legends of Leifeng Pagoda," divided into four panels: "King Qian Building the Pagoda," "Legend of White Snake," "Leifeng in Sunset Glow," and "Ancient Pagoda Reilluminated," with brilliant colors and exquisite brushwork. The first floor ground is paved with antique-style gold bricks, and the ceiling caisson is painted with celadon porcelain patterns from the Wuyue Kingdom.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_leifeng_pagoda_sa_03.png'),
  ('雷峰塔', 3, 'New Leifeng Pagoda Floors 2-4 (Xin Leifeng Ta Erzhi Siseng)', '新雷峰塔二至四层', '<p>Floors 2-4 of the new Leifeng Pagoda are located above the first floor and below the top-level viewing terrace, with each floor covering an area of about 600 square meters. They constitute the main body of the new pagoda''s cultural exhibition system and are also the core spaces for visitors to stop, appreciate, and rest during the ascent. The second floor''s theme is "Wuyue Buddhist Culture," displaying the prosperous scene of Buddhism in the Hangzhou region during the Wuyue Kingdom period and the Qian family''s reverence for Buddhism. The third floor''s theme is "Leifeng Pagoda and West Lake," displaying the interdependent relationship between Leifeng Pagoda and the West Lake scenic area throughout history through texts, images, old photographs, and multimedia. The fourth floor''s theme is "Qian Chu and Ancient Chinese Pagodas," systematically sorting out the architectural types of ancient Chinese pagodas and the architectural characteristics of the five precious pagodas whose construction was supervised by Qian Chu. Each floor is equipped with a circular viewing corridor.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_leifeng_pagoda_sa_04.png'),
  ('雷峰塔', 4, 'Leifeng Pagoda Top-Level Viewing Terrace (Leifeng Ta Dingceng Guanjing Tai)', '雷峰塔顶层观景台', '<p>The Leifeng Pagoda Top-Level Viewing Terrace is located at the highest point of the new pagoda (approximately at the fifth floor level, with a total height of about 70 meters). It is the viewing high point with the most open view in the Hangzhou West Lake scenic area and also the best viewing point for "Leifeng in Sunset Glow," one of the "Ten Scenes of West Lake." The viewing terrace features a fully open design with glass protective railings on all sides, allowing visitors a 360-degree unobstructed overlook of the complete view of West Lake. In the near view are the sparkling lake surface and the lush Gushan (Solitary Hill). To the east, one can clearly see Willow Wave Listening to Orioles, Duanqiao Canxue (Broken Bridge with Remnant Snow), and the urban skyline. To the south, one can see Flying Clouds over Jade Emperor Mountain and the layered greenery of Jiuyao Mountain. To the west lies the front view of Su Causeway in Spring Dawn, Flower Harbor Viewing Fish, and Three Pools Mirroring the Moon. To the north, one can even overlook Baochu Pagoda standing gracefully atop Precious Stone Hill——the two pagodas echoing each other from afar constitute the most core landscape pattern of West Lake. The viewing terrace is also equipped with electronic guide screens.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_leifeng_pagoda_sa_05.png'),
  ('雷峰塔', 5, 'Leifeng Pagoda Cultural Exhibition Hall (Leifeng Ta Wenhua Chenlieguan)', '雷峰塔文化陈列馆', '<p>The Leifeng Pagoda Cultural Exhibition Hall is located inside the Leifeng Pagoda scenic area entrance, adjacent to the mountain climbing walkway. It is an independent antique-style exhibition hall that officially opened to the public in 2004, synchronizing with the completion of the new Leifeng Pagoda reconstruction. The exhibition hall has a floor area of about 800 square meters, with the theme "Leifeng Pagoda and the Wuyue Kingdom," featuring four major exhibition sections that systematically showcase the long history of Leifeng Pagoda from its original construction in the Five Dynasties Wuyue Kingdom period to the present, spanning 1,025 years. The hall displays over 500 precious unearthed artifacts, including the Ashoka Tower (pure silver gilt, unearthed from the underground palace), gilt dragon lotus base, agate ornaments, stone carved sutra pillars, and brick Buddha statues, many of which are classified as national first-grade cultural relics. The exhibition hall also employs multimedia technology with surround projection to reappear the historical scene of Leifeng Pagoda''s collapse in 1924.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_leifeng_pagoda_sa_06.png'),
  ('雷峰塔', 6, 'Xizhao Pavilion and Release Pond (Xizhao Ting yu Fangsheng Chi)', '夕照亭与放生池', '<p>Xizhao Pavilion and Release Pond are located on the southeast side of the Leifeng Pagoda scenic area, constituting the core attraction for viewing "Leifeng in the Sunset Glow"—one of the Ten Scenes of West Lake. Xizhao Pavilion is a six-cornered pyramidal-roof classical pavilion, named after "Leifeng in the Sunset Glow" from the Ten Scenes of West Lake. The pavilion is equipped with stone tables and benches, making it the best spot for visitors to wait for sunset and photograph Leifeng Pagoda from a classic angle. The Release Pond is located in front of Xizhao Pavilion, with water drawn from West Lake. Lotus flowers are planted throughout the pond, and in summer the fragrance of lotus fills the air. A nine-arch stone bridge and a small Guanyin statue are set in the center of the pond. Visitors can purchase fish and turtles here for release activities, reflecting the Buddhist spirit of compassion. At dusk, when the setting sun descends and rosy clouds illuminate Leifeng Pagoda, the pagoda body presents a brilliant golden-red glow.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_leifeng_pagoda_sa_07.png'),
  ('良渚古城遗址公园', 0, 'Liangzhu Ancient City Heritage Park South Entrance (Nanrukou)', '良渚古城遗址公园南入口', '<p>The South Entrance of Liangzhu Ancient City Heritage Park is located at the intersection of Fengdu Road and National Highway 104 in Yuhang District, Hangzhou. It is the main entrance of the park and the first stop for visitors entering this sacred land of 5,000-year civilization. The entrance building complex adopts the "jade cong" shape, inspired by the cong——the most representative jade artifact of Liangzhu culture. The yellowish-brown exterior walls perfectly blend with the surrounding rice paddies and water networks, reflecting the advanced conservation philosophy of "protecting heritage through parkification." Inside the visitor center are comprehensive service hall, heritage museum shop, rest area, and multimedia guide hall, providing Chinese-English guide maps, audio guide rental (approx. 30 RMB/unit), and barrier-free services.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_liangzhu_ancient_city_sa_01.png'),
  ('良渚古城遗址公园', 1, 'Land Gate Ruins (Lüchengmen Yizhi)', '陆城门遗址', '<p>The Land Gate Ruins are located in the central part of Liangzhu Ancient City Heritage Park, at the convergence of the south city wall and east city wall. They are the only land gate ruins of Liangzhu Ancient City that remain above ground, and also one of the earliest known prehistorical earthen city gate ruins globally. The city gate ruin is a massive loess terrace base about 40 meters wide east-west and 30 meters deep north-south. On the terrace base, clear pillar grooves and mud-and-wood wall traces are preserved. Based on this, archaeologists infer that this was originally a heavy timber city gate building with seven bays in width and three bays in depth. A protective large-span steel structure shed has been built above the ruins. Visitors can walk along the elevated wooden plank road for a circular visit. Every autumn, the rice paddies around the city gate ruins turn a golden yellow, creating an interesting contrast with the loess city gate——one of the most classic photography spots in the heritage park.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_liangzhu_ancient_city_sa_02.png'),
  ('良渚古城遗址公园', 2, 'Water Gate Ruins (Shuichengmen Yizhi)', '水城门遗址', '<p>The Water Gate Ruins are located in the northern part of Liangzhu Ancient City Heritage Park, north of the Mojiaoshan Palace Area. They are one of the most representative ruins of the "water city" layout of Liangzhu Ancient City. Unlike ancient cities in the Central Plains region which were primarily land-based, Liangzhu Ancient City was a "water city" built on swampy wetland, with crisscrossing waterways and developed water systems inside and outside the city. Therefore, water gates became the main transportation access to the outside world. The existing water gate ruins consist of a river channel gap about 30 meters wide. On both sides of the river channel, neatly rammed loess gate piers are preserved, and pillar hole arrangements are faintly discernible atop the piers, indicating that heavy timber water gate structures once existed here. The Water Gate Ruins are displayed in their original open-air condition without a protective shed.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_liangzhu_ancient_city_sa_03.png'),
  ('良渚古城遗址公园', 3, 'South City Wall Ruins (Nanchengqiang Yizhi)', '南城墙遗址', '<p>The South City Wall Ruins are located in the southern part of Liangzhu Ancient City Heritage Park, west of the Land Gate Ruins. They are the best-preserved and most completely displayed section among the four sides of city walls of Liangzhu Ancient City. The city wall ruins run east-west, with a remaining length of about 500 meters, remaining width of about 20-40 meters, and remaining height of about 2-4 meters. The wall body was constructed by layering yellow clay and gravel for ramming, with the rammed layers clearly distinguishable, reflecting the superb civil engineering technology of the Liangzhu people. A protective wooden long shed has been built above the ruins. In the middle section of the south city wall, a "city wall cross-section display window" is also preserved. The south city wall is an excellent window for understanding the construction technology of Liangzhu Ancient City.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_liangzhu_ancient_city_sa_04.png'),
  ('良渚古城遗址公园', 4, 'Zhongjiagang Ancient River Channel (Zhongjiagang Guhedao)', '钟家港古河道', '<p>Zhongjiagang Ancient River Channel is located in the central part of Liangzhu Ancient City Heritage Park, east of the Mojiaoshan Palace Area. It is the most important north-south ancient river channel inside Liangzhu Ancient City and also one of the ruin sites with the richest unearthed artifacts from Liangzhu Ancient City archaeology to date. The ancient river channel has a total length of about 1,000 meters, with the existing riverbed width of about 15-25 meters. The river channel interior preserves a Liangzhu culture accumulation layer up to 3 meters thick. Archaeologists have conducted multiple large-scale excavations here, unearthing jade semi-finished products, stone yue (battle-axes), stone plows, wooden artifacts, bone artifacts, pottery shards, and some jade raw materials. A fully enclosed steel structure protective exhibition hall has been built above the ancient river channel. Inside the exhibition hall, the temperature and humidity are constant.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_liangzhu_ancient_city_sa_05.png'),
  ('良渚古城遗址公园', 5, 'Mojiaoshan Palace Ruins (Mojiaoshan Dianzhang Yizhi)', '莫角山宫殿遗址', '<p>The Mojiaoshan Palace Ruins are located at the center-north position of Liangzhu Ancient City Heritage Park. They are the core, highest-grade architectural ruins of Liangzhu Ancient City, and also the largest known palace terrace base from the prehistorical period in Chinese history. The ruins consist of a massive artificial loess high platform, about 630 meters long east-west, 450 meters wide north-south, and 10 meters high in remaining height, with an earthwork volume exceeding one million cubic meters. On the high platform, three groups of large palace foundation sites arranged east-west are preserved. Among these, the "Da Mojiaoshan" palace foundation site covers an area of about 30,000 square meters. It was originally a heavy timber-and-earthen structure palace complex with over ten bays in width and four to five bays in depth——the "Forbidden City" from 5,000 years ago. A massive steel structure protective shed has been built above the ruins.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_liangzhu_ancient_city_sa_06.png'),
  ('良渚古城遗址公园', 6, 'Fanshan Royal Tomb (Fanshan Wangling)', '反山王陵', '<p>The Fanshan Royal Tomb is located on the west side of Liangzhu Ancient City Heritage Park, about 200 meters northwest of the Mojiaoshan Palace Area. It is the highest-grade known royal tomb ruin site of Liangzhu culture and one of the most significant archaeological discoveries of Liangzhu Ancient City. The royal tomb is an artificial earthen platform in the shape of an inverted bucket, about 70 meters long, 30 meters wide, and 6 meters high. Eleven large tombs from the late Liangzhu culture period are distributed on the platform top, among which Tomb No. 9 belonged to the principal personage——a king of the ancient Liangzhu Kingdom. In 1986, archaeologists conducted large-scale excavations here, unearthing over 1,200 pieces (sets) of various jade artifacts including jade cong, jade bi, jade yue (battle-axe), and jade crest ornaments.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_liangzhu_ancient_city_sa_07.png'),
  ('良渚古城遗址公园', 7, 'Jiangjiashan Aristocratic Cemetery (Jiangjiashan Guizu Mudiji)', '姜家山贵族墓地', '<p>The Jiangjiashan Aristocratic Cemetery is located in the northwest part of Liangzhu Ancient City Heritage Park, about 300 meters north of the Fanshan Royal Tomb. It is the high-grade aristocratic tomb area inside Liangzhu Ancient City, second only to the Fanshan Royal Tomb. The cemetery ruins consist of an artificial loess terrace, about 100 meters long and 40 meters wide. Fourteen medium-sized tombs from the late Liangzhu culture period are distributed on the terrace top. The tomb owners were mostly aristocrats of the ancient Liangzhu Kingdom——including high-ranking military generals, close relatives of the royal family, and grand sacrificial priests. Over 600 pieces of various funerary objects were unearthed from the tombs, including jade cong, jade bi, jade yue, stone yue, pottery, and lacquerware. A protective shed has been built above the cemetery ruins, with an elevated wooden plank road for visiting inside.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_liangzhu_ancient_city_sa_08.png'),
  ('良渚古城遗址公园', 8, 'Meirendi Ruins (Meirendi Yizhi)', '美人地遗址', '<p>The Meirendi Ruins are located in the southeast part of Liangzhu Ancient City Heritage Park, east of the Zhongjiagang Ancient River Channel. They are representative archaeological ruins of ordinary residential areas inside Liangzhu Ancient City. In sharp contrast to the grand specifications of the Mojiaoshan Palace Area and Fanshan Royal Tomb, the Meirendi Ruins display the appearance of "commoner community" from 5,000 years ago. The ruins area preserves dense column hole groups of stilt-style buildings, hearth pit ruins, garbage dumping pits, and small family cemeteries. Large quantities of carbonized rice grains, pottery shards, stone tools, and bone tools were unearthed, vividly reappearing the daily life scene of Liangzhu ancestors "eating rice and fish soup, building stilt houses for dwelling." The ruins area name "Meirendi" (Beauty''s Place) originates from local folklore. An open-style protective shed has been built above the ruins.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_liangzhu_ancient_city_sa_09.png'),
  ('良渚古城遗址公园', 9, 'Zhishan Viewing Platform (Zhishan Guanjing Tai)', '雉山观景台', '<p>The Zhishan Viewing Platform is located at the northernmost end of Liangzhu Ancient City Heritage Park, on the summit of Zhishan Hill, at an altitude of about 65 meters. It is the highest point within the heritage park and also the best location for overlooking the full view of Liangzhu Ancient City. The viewing platform is a steel-structure double-story eight-cornered pavilion. Standing on the bottom-floor circular corridor of the viewing platform, you can take in the complete view of Liangzhu Ancient City. The top-floor multimedia exhibition hall is equipped with a surround projection system. Through a 15-minute 4D animation demonstration, it completely reappears the entire historical process of Liangzhu Ancient City from site selection and city construction, through peak prosperity, to gradual decline. It is the best window for visitors to understand the macroscopic course of Liangzhu civilization. The viewing platform is also equipped with high-power telescopes (charged at approx. 10 RMB per use).</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_liangzhu_ancient_city_sa_10.png'),
  ('灵隐寺', 0, 'Lingyin Temple Scenic Area Entrance (Lingyin Jingqu Rukou)', '灵隐寺景区入口', '<p>The Lingyin Temple Scenic Area Entrance is located at 1 Fazhou Alley, Xihu District, Hangzhou, and is the formal starting point for entering the Lingyin Temple Scenic Area and Feilai Peak Carved Statues area. A large bluestone paifang (memorial archway) is set up at the entrance, with the four large characters "Lingyin Zen Traces" inscribed on the archway plaque in a vigorous and antique style, calligraphed by Li Ruihuan, former Chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People''s Political Consultative Conference. Inside the entrance are visitor center, ticket office (Feilai Peak scenic area 45 RMB/person, Lingyin Temple charges an additional 30 RMB incense offering fee), luggage storage, and barrier-free access——complete facilities and thoughtful service. From the entrance to the Lingyin Temple mountain gate, it takes about 5-8 minutes of walking.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_lingyin_temple_sa_01.png'),
  ('灵隐寺', 1, 'Feilai Peak Carved Statues (Feilai Feng Zaoiang)', '飞来峰造像', '<p>Feilai Peak Carved Statues are located east of the Lingyin Temple Scenic Area entrance, in front of Lingyin Temple''s mountain gate. They are the largest in scale and best-preserved statue group among West Lake cliffside carved art, and also a Major Historical and Cultural Site Protected at the National Level. Feilai Peak is also known as "Spiritual Vulture Peak," about 168 meters high, with over 470 cliffside carved statues from the Five Dynasties to Yuan Dynasty distributed among the rock walls. The most famous is the Song Dynasty seated Maitreya Buddha statue, bare-chested and big-bellied with an ever-smiling mouth. The statue group is distributed along both banks of the creek valley, with towering ancient trees and hanging vines.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_lingyin_temple_sa_02.png'),
  ('灵隐寺', 2, 'Ligong Pagoda and Lengquan Pavilion (Ligong Ta yu Lengquan Ting)', '理公塔与冷泉亭', '<p>Ligong Pagoda and Lengquan Pavilion are located in front of Lingyin Temple''s mountain gate, west of Feilai Peak Carved Statues. They are the scenic combination with the richest cultural heritage within the Lingyin Temple Scenic Area. Ligong Pagoda is also known as "Lingyin Pagoda" and was built to commemorate Ven. Huili, the founding patriarch of Lingyin Temple. Huili traveled to Hangzhou in 326 CE (first year of the Xianhe reign of Eastern Jin) and, seeing the mountain''s exquisite beauty as if the Spiritual Vulture Peak from India had flown here, built a temple facing the mountain, naming it "Lingyin" (Soul''s Retreat). Ligong Pagoda is a six-cornered, seven-story pavilion-style solid stone pagoda, about 8 meters high. Lengquan Pavilion is located south of Ligong Pagoda, by the bank of Lengquan Creek.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_lingyin_temple_sa_03.png'),
  ('灵隐寺', 3, 'Hall of Heavenly Kings (Tianwang Dian)', '天王殿', '<p>The Hall of Heavenly Kings is the first main hall after Lingyin Temple''s mountain gate and the first hall on the temple''s central axis. It was first built during the Five Dynasties period of the Wuyue Kingdom, and the existing hall was rebuilt in modern times. The hall spans seven bays in width and four bays in depth, with a double-eave xieshan roof covered with yellow glazed tiles. Enshrined in the center of the hall is the incarnation of Maitreya Bodhisattva——the bare-chested, big-bellied, ever-smiling Maitreya Buddha seated statue, about 2.5 meters high, carved from camphor wood in the Qing Dynasty and fully gilded. On both sides of the hall are enshrined the majestic statues of the Four Heavenly Kings, respectively governing wind, harmony, rain, and smoothness, implying "favorable weather, the country peaceful and the people safe."</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_lingyin_temple_sa_04.png'),
  ('灵隐寺', 4, 'Mahavira Hall (Daxiong Baodian)', '大雄宝殿', '<p>The Mahavira Hall is located behind the Hall of Heavenly Kings, at the core position of Lingyin Temple''s central axis. It is the largest in scale and highest in specification among the halls in the temple, and also one of the most splendid and magnificent halls in Chinese Buddhist temples. The hall spans nine bays in width and five bays in depth, with a double-eave hipped roof——the highest grade of ancient Chinese building roof form——covered with yellow glazed tiles. Enshrined in the center of the hall is the gilded wood-carved seated statue of Sakyamuni Buddha, with a statue height of about 24.8 meters (including the Sumeru throne and auspicious backdrop), fully gilded with a solemn and majestic appearance. It is currently the largest indoor wood-carved Buddha statue within China''s borders.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_lingyin_temple_sa_05.png'),
  ('灵隐寺', 5, 'Medicine Buddha Hall (Yaoshi Dian)', '药师殿', '<p>The Medicine Buddha Hall is located on the east side of the Mahavira Hall on Lingyin Temple''s central axis. It is the side hall specifically dedicated to Medicine Buddha of the Eastern Pure Lapis Lazuli World, and also the hall most favored by Hangzhou devotees for praying to dispel disasters, extend lifespan, and maintain physical health. The hall spans five bays in width and three bays in depth, with a single-eave xieshan roof, black tiles, and vermilion pillars——simple, elegant, and dignified in style. Enshrined in the center of the hall is the seated statue of Medicine Buddha, about 3.5 meters high, wearing Buddhist robes and holding a medicine vase, with a compassionate and serene countenance. The hall''s front courtyard is planted with a medicinal herb garden, growing dozens of Chinese medicinal herbs such as Ganoderma lucidum, Chinese angelica, and Astragalus membranaceus——a unique "Buddhist medicinal herb garden" landscape in Lingyin Temple.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_lingyin_temple_sa_06.png'),
  ('灵隐寺', 6, 'Scripture Library (Cangjing Lou)', '藏经楼', '<p>The Scripture Library is located at the northernmost end of Lingyin Temple''s central axis, behind the Mahavira Hall. It is the hall specifically used for collecting and enshrining the Buddhist Tripitaka and precious Buddhist scriptures, as well as an important venue for the abbot to preach the Dharma and for monastics to study scriptures in daily practice. The library is a two-story building with five bays in width and four bays in depth, featuring a double-eave ying-shan roof with green tiles and white walls, presenting an elegant and dignified style. Enshrined in the center of the first floor is a large reclining jade Buddha from Myanmar, over 6 meters in length—the largest jade Buddha statue in the temple. The second floor is the scripture collection area, housing precious Tripitaka versions such as the "Qianlong Tripitaka," "Yongle Northern Tripitaka," and "Fangshan Stone Scriptures," as well as handwritten manuscripts of treatises by eminent monks across dynasties.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_lingyin_temple_sa_07.png'),
  ('灵隐寺', 7, 'Huayan Hall (Huayan Dian)', '华严殿', '<p>The Huayan Hall is located on the west side of Lingyin Temple''s central axis, south of the Scripture Library. It is the hall dedicated to the Huayan Three Sages. The Huayan Three Sages feature Vairocana Buddha (Dharma Body Buddha) in the center, Manjusri Bodhisattva (Wisdom Virtue) on the left, and Samantabhadra Bodhisattva (Principle Virtue) on the right, together demonstrating the perfect and harmonious Dharma Realm view of "one is all, all is one" from the Huayan Sutra. The hall spans five bays in width and three bays in depth, with a single-eave xieshan roof and vermilion pillars—dignified and elegant in style. Inside the hall, the three Buddha statues are each about 4 meters high, carved from camphor wood and fully gilded.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_lingyin_temple_sa_08.png'),
  ('灵隐寺', 8, 'Jigong Hall (Jigong Dian)', '济公殿', '<p>The Jigong Hall is located in the east side hall of Lingyin Temple and is the dedicated hall commemorating Ven. Jigong (secular name Li Xiuyuan, Dharma name Chan Master Daoji) of the Southern Song Dynasty. Jigong was born in 1148 CE (18th year of the Shaoxing reign) in Tiantai County. At age 18, he became a monk under Ven. Xiaotang Huiyuan at Lingyin Temple. He is widely known for his "crazy" image—"shoes torn, hat torn, kasaya on the body torn"—and his transcendent state of "wine and meat pass through the intestines, but the Buddha remains in the heart," revered by the people as the "Living Buddha Jigong." Enshrined in the center of the hall is the seated statue of Jigong, about 2.5 meters high, wearing a tattered kasaya and holding a broken fan, with a humorous and approachable expression.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_lingyin_temple_sa_09.png'),
  ('灵隐寺', 9, 'Hall of Five Hundred Arhats (Wubai Luohan Tang)', '五百罗汉堂', '<p>The Hall of Five Hundred Arhats is located in the west side hall of Lingyin Temple and is the dedicated hall for enshrining the Five Hundred Arhats, also one of the larger and better-preserved Arhat Halls among Hangzhou temples. The Arhat Hall spans seven bays in width and three bays in depth, with a single-eave hipped roof, green tiles, and vermilion pillars—dignified yet elegant in architectural style. Inside the hall, shrines for the Five Hundred Arhats are arranged along three walls, each Arhat statue about 0.8 meters in height, round-carved from camphor wood and fully gilded. The Arhats have diverse expressions and are vividly lifelike. In the center of the hall are enshrined Vairocana Buddha and the two Bodhisattvas Manjusri and Samantabhadra, forming the "Three Sages of Huayan" configuration. The four walls of the Arhat Hall are also painted with Buddhist story frescoes.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_lingyin_temple_sa_10.png'),
  ('六和塔', 0, 'Liuhe Pagoda Scenic Area Entrance (Liuhe Ta Jingqu Rukou)', '六和塔景区入口', '<p>The Liuhe Pagoda Scenic Area Entrance is located at 16 Zhijiang Road, Xihu District, Hangzhou, and is the formal starting point for entering the Liuhe Pagoda Scenic Area and visiting Liuhe Pagoda. The entrance is paved with neat bluestone slab steps, with a gate house featuring a five-bay, double-eave xieshan roof antique-style building, complete with black tiles, vermilion pillars, and upturned eaves. A horizontal plaque inscribed with the three large characters "Liuhe Pagoda" hangs at the entrance, presenting a dignified bearing. The entrance square is equipped with a scenic area introduction stone tablet, tour guide map, and electronic ticket office.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_liuhe_pagoda_sa_01.png'),
  ('六和塔', 1, 'Liuhe Pagoda (Liuhe Ta)', '六和塔', '<p>Liuhe Pagoda is located atop Yuelun Peak in Xihu District, Hangzhou, on the north bank of the Qiantang River. It was first built in 970 CE (third year of the Kaibao reign of Northern Song) under the supervision of King Qian Chu of Wuyue Kingdom, who ordered its construction to supress the tidal bore of the Qiantang River. The pagoda derived its name from the Buddhist concept of "Six Harmonies and Respect"—body harmoniously dwelling together, speech harmoniously non-contending, mind harmoniously delighted together, precepts harmoniously jointly cultivated, views harmoniously jointly understood, and benefits harmoniously equally shared. The pagoda stands about 59.89 meters high with thirteen levels (seven levels in exterior appearance, thirteen levels in interior division), adopting a brick-wood structure.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_liuhe_pagoda_sa_02.png'),
  ('六和塔', 2, 'Pagoda Foundation and Underground Palace (Taji yu Diogong)', '塔基与地宫', '<p>The Pagoda Foundation and Underground Palace are located at the base of Liuhe Pagoda and constitute the core space for the protective exhibition of the pagoda''s foundation ruins and interment structure. The Liuhe Pagoda foundation is a massive rammed-earth high platform, about 40 meters on each side and 2.5 meters high. A protective steel structure shed has been built above the pagoda foundation. Visitors can walk along the elevated wooden plank road for a circular visit, and through professional information signs, understand the "pagoda covering ruins" conservation philosophy of Liuhe Pagoda and the interment system for ancient pagoda construction.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_liuhe_pagoda_sa_03.png'),
  ('六和塔', 3, 'Pagoda Body Floors 1-7 (Tashen Diyizhi Qiceng)', '塔身一至七层', '<p>Liuhe Pagoda has a total of thirteen levels (seven levels in exterior appearance, thirteen levels in interior division), among which floors 1-7 are open to visitors for ascending. Each floor covers an area of about 200-300 square meters and constitutes the core space for cultural relic display and viewing experience in Liuhe Pagoda. The first floor''s theme is "Liuhe Pagoda and King Qian''s Pagoda Construction," displaying Wuyue Kingdom history and the origin of pagoda construction. Floors 2-6 have the theme "Buddhist Art and Qiantang River Culture," displaying Song Dynasty Buddhist sculptures, frescoes, sutra scrolls, and Qiantang River poetry and calligraphy floor by floor. The seventh floor is a 360-degree open viewing terrace.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_liuhe_pagoda_sa_04.png'),
  ('六和塔', 4, 'Pagoda Top-Level Viewing Terrace (Tadingceng Guanjing Tai)', '塔顶层观景台', '<p>The Top-Level Viewing Terrace is located at the highest point of Liuhe Pagoda (7th floor) and is the viewing high point with the most open view in the Hangzhou Qiantang River scenic area, also the most震撼力 (shocking/impressive) river scenery viewing point beyond the "Ten Scenes of Hangzhou." The viewing terrace features a fully open design with wooden corridors and viewing windows on all sides, allowing visitors a 360-degree unobstructed overlook. In the near view is the majestic Qiantang River Bridge (double-deck road-rail combined bridge) and the surging river water. Every year around the 18th day of the 8th lunar month during the Qiantang River tidal bore season, the top floor of Liuhe Pagoda is one of the best tidal viewing points.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_liuhe_pagoda_sa_05.png'),
  ('六和塔', 5, 'Liuhe Pagoda Cultural Exhibition Hall (Liuh e Ta Wenhua Chenlieguan)', '六和塔文化陈列馆', '<p>The Liuhe Pagoda Cultural Exhibition Hall is located inside the Liuhe Pagoda scenic area entrance, adjacent to the mountain climbing walkway. It is an independent antique-style exhibition hall that officially opened to the public in 1991, synchronizing with the completion of the major renovation of Liuhe Pagoda. The exhibition hall has a floor area of about 600 square meters, with the theme "Liuhe Pagoda and the Wuyue Kingdom," featuring four major exhibition sections that systematically showcase the long history of Liuhe Pagoda from its original construction in 970 CE (third year of Kaibao reign of Northern Song) to the present, spanning 1,054 years. The hall displays over 300 precious unearthed artifacts, including Ashoka Tower (gilt copper, unearthed from the underground palace), stone carved sutra pillars, agate ornaments, brick Buddha statues, and "Kaiyuan Tongbao" copper coins.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_liuhe_pagoda_sa_06.png'),
  ('六和塔', 6, 'Chinese Ancient Pagoda Exhibition Garden (Zhonghua Guta Bolanyuan)', '中华古塔博览苑', '<p>The Chinese Ancient Pagoda Exhibition Garden is located in the central part of the Liuhe Pagoda scenic area, south of Liuhe Pagoda. It is a thematic garden with the theme of displaying Chinese ancient pagoda architectural art, officially opened to the public in 1997. The Exhibition Garden covers an area of about 1.5 hectares, and according to the regional distribution and architectural types of Chinese ancient pagodas, assembles over a hundred miniature models of famous ancient pagodas from all over the country, including Big Wild Goose Pagoda, Small Wild Goose Pagoda, Yingxian Wooden Pagoda, Songyue Temple Pagoda, Feihong Pagoda, and Zhenjue Temple Vajra Throne Pagoda. The pagoda heights range from 1 meter to 8 meters, with materials covering brick, stone, wood, copper, and iron, completely presenting the architectural evolution process and regional style differences of Chinese ancient pagodas.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_liuhe_pagoda_sa_07.png'),
  ('六和塔', 7, 'Qiantang River Viewing Platform (Qiantang Jiang Guanjing Pingtai)', '钱塘江观景平台', '<p>The Qiantang River Viewing Platform is located at the southernmost end of the Liuhe Pagoda scenic area, on the mountain cliff south of Yuelun Peak. It is a semi-open viewing platform and also the viewing point with the most open view for observing the river within the Liuhe Pagoda scenic area. The platform is a reinforced concrete structure, with the surface paved with antique-style bluestone slabs, and cement faux-wood railings around it, able to accommodate about 50 people for viewing simultaneously. Standing on the platform, you can take in the entire Qiantang River——in the near view is the majestic Qiantang River Bridge (double-deck road-rail combined bridge) and the surging river water. Every year around the 18th day of the 8th lunar month during the Qiantang River tidal bore season, the viewing platform is one of the secondary tidal viewing points.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_liuhe_pagoda_sa_08.png'),
  ('六和塔', 8, 'Liuhe Bell Sound (Liuhe Zhongsheng)', '六合钟声', '<p>The Liuhe Bell Sound is located inside the Liuhe Pagoda scenic area entrance, at the starting point of the mountain climbing walkway. It is a combination of an independent double-eave six-cornered bell tower and a giant bronze bell. The bell tower is an all-wood structure, about 12 meters high, with a double-eave six-cornered pyramidal roof, black tiles, and vermilion pillars——dignified and elegant in style. Inside the tower hangs a giant bronze bell, about 2.5 meters high, 1.8 meters in diameter, and weighing about 5 tons. Visitors can purchase tickets (approx. 20 RMB/person) to personally hold a wooden mallet and strike the bell. Every New Year''s Eve, the Liuhe Pagoda scenic area hosts the "New Year Bell Sound" activity.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_liuhe_pagoda_sa_09.png'),
  ('六和塔', 9, 'Stele Pavilion (Beiting)', '碑亭', '<p>The Stele Pavilion is located north of Liuhe Pagoda, on the platform below the pagoda foundation. It is a Jiangnan classical pavilion building with a single-eave four-cornered pyramidal roof, specially built to protect the stele inscriptions recording pagoda repair events across dynasties. Inside the pavilion stand five steles recording the events of repairing Liuhe Pagoda across dynasties. The earliest is the "Record of Repairing Liuhe Pagoda" stele from 1153 CE (23rd year of the Shaoxing reign of Southern Song). The most precious is the "Record of Repairing Liuhe Pagoda" stele from 1523 CE (2nd year of the Jiajing reign of Ming Dynasty). The Stele Pavilion building is small, exquisite, and equipped with stone seating on all sides.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_liuhe_pagoda_sa_10.png'),
  ('千岛湖景区', 0, 'Qiandaohu Central Lake Area Tourist Dock (Qiandaohu Zhongxin Huqu Lüyou Matou)', '千岛湖中心湖区旅游码头', '<p>The Qiandaohu Central Lake Area Tourist Dock is located on Xin''an Avenue in Qiandaohu Town, Chun''an County, Hangzhou. It is the most core and facility-complete tourist distribution dock in the Qiandaohu scenic area, and also the departure hub for tourists to take cruise ships to visit the central lake area (Meifeng Island, Yule Island, Longshan Island, Moonlight Island). The dock is equipped with a large modern passenger waiting hall, complete with air conditioning, seating, electronic display screens, and ticket windows, dispatching over 3 million passengers annually. Departing from the central lake area dock, visitors can take cruise ships of different grades (approx. 150-300 RMB/person) for a tour around the lake, passing core scenic spots such as Meifeng Island, Yule Island, Longshan Island, and Moonlight Island, with a total duration of about 8 hours.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_qiandao_lake_sa_01.png'),
  ('千岛湖景区', 1, 'Meifeng Island (Meifeng Dao)', '梅峰岛', '<p>Meifeng Island is located on the northwest side of Qiandaohu''s central lake area, about 8 kilometers from the central lake area dock. It is the viewing island with the most open view and most magnificent scenery among Qiandaohu''s 1,078 islands, with the saying "If you don''t ascend Meifeng to view the archipelago, you won''t know the true face of Qiandao Lake." The island is about 204 meters high. After landing at the dock, visitors need to walk or take the cable car (approx. 30 RMB/person) up to the summit viewing platform, taking about 20-30 minutes total. A 360-degree open viewing platform is set up on the mountain summit. The best photography times for Meifeng Island are early morning and dusk.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_qiandao_lake_sa_02.png'),
  ('千岛湖景区', 2, 'Yule Island (Yule Dao)', '渔乐岛', '<p>Yule Island is located in the central part of Qiandaohu''s central lake area, between Meifeng Island and Longshan Island, about 6 kilometers from the central lake area dock. The island name "Yule" is derived from the meaning "the joy of fishermen, joy all around." The entire island takes fish culture as its theme. The island is equipped with a lakeside view restaurant serving Qiandaohu organic fish head soup, Chun''an rice soup, and various lake-fresh stir-fries. Yule Island is also the concentration point for Qiandaohu water activities.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_qiandao_lake_sa_03.png'),
  ('千岛湖景区', 3, 'Longshan Island (Longshan Dao)', '龙山岛', '<p>Longshan Island is located on the south side of Qiandaohu''s central lake area, about 4 kilometers from the central lake area dock. The island name "Longshan (Dragon Mountain)" originates from the small hill at the center of Chun''an ancient county seat——Longshan. After the Xin''an River Reservoir impounded water in 1959 and Chun''an ancient county seat was submerged beneath the lake, the summit of Longshan happened to emerge above the water surface, becoming the only landmark remnant of the ancient county seat. The core landscape on the island is Hairui Shrine, first built in 1562 (41st year of the Jiajing reign of Ming Dynasty) to commemorate Hairui, the upright official who once served as magistrate of Chun''an County. The island also serves as an important window for understanding the "underwater ancient city" culture of Qiandaohu.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_qiandao_lake_sa_04.png'),
  ('千岛湖景区', 4, 'Hairui Shrine (Hairui Ci)', '海瑞祠', '<p>Hairui Shrine is located in the central part of Longshan Island in Qiandaohu''s central lake area. It is a thematic shrine built to commemorate Hairui, the upright official of the Ming Dynasty, and also the core of Longshan Island''s cultural landscape. Hairui (1514-1587 CE), courtesy name Ruxian, literary name Gangfeng, was from Qiongshan (today''s Haikou), Hainan. He served as magistrate of Chun''an County in 1566 (45th year of the Jiajing reign). During his tenure, he maintained integrity, cracked down on powerful local clans, and redressed unjust cases, deeply loved by the common people and hailed as "Hai the Blue Sky." The shrine is a Ming-Qing style courtyard-style building with three sections and two skywells, featuring black tiles, white walls, and carved wood doors——dignified and elegantly simple.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_qiandao_lake_sa_05.png'),
  ('千岛湖景区', 5, 'Moonlight Island (Yueguang Dao)', '月光岛', '<p>Moonlight Island is located on the northeast side of Qiandaohu''s central lake area, about 7 kilometers from the central lake dock, formed by four green islands connected head-to-tail. It is the most romantic island in Qiandaohu. The island takes "moonlight" as its theme, with four major functional zones: the Moon Matchmaker Temple, Moon-Viewing Pavilion, Dream-Moon Pavilion, and New Moon Slope. The Moon Matchmaker Temple enshrines the Old Man Under the Moon, a popular destination for couples to pray for marriage. The Moon-Viewing Pavilion is a six-cornered classical pavilion and the best moon-viewing spot on the island.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_qiandao_lake_sa_06.png'),
  ('千岛湖景区', 6, 'Lock Island (Suo Dao)', '锁岛', '<p>Lock Island is located in the central lake area of Qiandaohu, situated in the lake section connecting Meifeng Island and Yule Island. It is one of the most fun and interactive islands in Qiandaohu. The entire island takes "lock" as its core cultural imagery. A 300-meter Lock Culture Corridor is set up along the island, with walls and display racks on both sides悬挂 tens of thousands of locks ranging from bronze locks from the Spring and Autumn Period, iron locks from the Han Dynasty, silver locks from the Tang Dynasty, to modern fingerprint locks, password locks, and facial recognition locks. The "Lock King" on the island weighs one ton and is about 2.5 meters high.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_qiandao_lake_sa_07.png'),
  ('千岛湖景区', 7, 'Zhuangyuan Bridge (Zhuangyuan Qiao)', '状元桥', '<p>Zhuangyuan Bridge connects Lock Island and Bird Island in Qiandaohu. It is a chain suspension bridge spanning between the two islands, with a total length of about 230 meters and a height difference of about 16 meters from the lake surface. The bridge name "Zhuangyuan" originates from the "Zhuangyuan" (top scholar) in China''s ancient imperial examination system——the first-place winner of the palace examination, implying "success in the imperial examination and rising step by step." Every year before the high school entrance exam (zhongkao) and college entrance exam (gaokao), large numbers of students and parents make special trips to walk across Zhuangyuan Bridge.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_qiandao_lake_sa_08.png'),
  ('千岛湖景区', 8, 'Wenxin Island (Wenxin Dao)', '温馨岛', '<p>Wenxin Island is located in the southeast lake area of Qiandaohu, about 12 kilometers from Qiandaohu Town. It is one of the earliest islands in Qiandaohu to develop vacation businesses and currently the island with the most comprehensive vacation functions. The entire island covers an area of about 120 mu. A Wenxin Island Vacation Hotel built to four-star standard is on the island, with over 120 lakeview guest rooms, a conference center, dining halls, and a water sports center. The west side of the island has a large yacht dock and various water sports facilities.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_qiandao_lake_sa_09.png'),
  ('千岛湖景区', 9, 'Huangshanjian in Southeast Lake Area (Dongnan Hujqu Huangshanjian)', '东南湖区黄山尖', '<p>Huangshanjian is located in the southeast lake area of Qiandaohu, about 20 kilometers from Qiandaohu Town, with an elevation of about 266 meters. It is the highest peak in the southeast lake area and one of the most stunning viewing spots in Qiandaohu. Taking the cable car from the mountain foot to the summit takes about 8 minutes. A 360-degree open viewing platform is set up on the mountain summit. Standing on the viewing platform, you can take in the densely distributed island group of the southeast lake area of Qiandaohu.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_qiandao_lake_sa_10.png'),
  ('中国丝绸博物馆', 0, 'China National Silk Museum Entrance (Zhongguo Sichou Bowuguan Rukou)', '中国丝绸博物馆入口', '<p>The China National Silk Museum Entrance is located at 73-1 Yuhuangshan Road, Xihu District, Hangzhou, and is the formal starting point for entering this national-level thematic museum. The entrance is paved with neat bluestone slab steps, with a gate house featuring a five-bay, double-eave xieshan roof antique-style building, complete with black tiles, vermilion pillars, and upturned eaves. A horizontal plaque inscribed with the nine large gilded characters "China National Silk Museum" hangs at the entrance, presenting a dignified bearing. Inside the entrance are comprehensive service hall, museum shop, rest area, and multimedia guide hall, providing Chinese-English guide maps, audio guide rental (approx. 30 RMB/unit), and barrier-free services.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_silk_museum_sa_01.png'),
  ('中国丝绸博物馆', 1, 'Silk Road Gallery: The Story of Chinese Silk', '丝路馆：中国丝绸故事', '<p>The Silk Road Gallery is the core permanent exhibition hall of the China National Silk Museum, located on the second floor of the main building, with a floor area of about 2,000 square meters. The exhibition takes "The Story of Chinese Silk" as its theme, divided into five major sections according to historical chronology: "Origin of Silk," "Silk Road in Han and Tang," "Silk in Song and Yuan," "Silk in Ming and Qing," and "Modern Silk." The gallery displays over a thousand pieces of silk cultural relics from the Neolithic Period to the present, including the Warring States period silk fragment, the Han Dynasty "Five Stars Rise in the East, Benefiting China" brocade arm guard, Tang Dynasty pearl-roundel paired-duck patterned brocade, Song Dynasty kesi (silk tapestry) flower-bird painting, Yuan Dynasty gold-threaded brocade, and Ming Dynasty doumiu robe—all crown jewels of the collection. The exhibition hall employs immersive multimedia display methods.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_silk_museum_sa_02.png'),
  ('中国丝绸博物馆', 2, 'Silkworm and Mulberry Gallery (Cansang Guan)', '蚕桑馆', '<p>The Silkworm and Mulberry Gallery is located on the east side of the first floor of the main building of the China National Silk Museum, with a floor area of about 800 square meters. It is the only thematic exhibition hall in China and abroad with "silkworm and mulberry" as its theme. The exhibition is divided into three major sections: "The Life Cycle of Silkworms," "Mulberry and Sericulture," and "Silk Reeling and the Silk Road." Inside the gallery, the complete life process from silkworm egg hatching, larval molting, cocoon-spinning, to emerging from the cocoon as a moth is fully recreated through large-scale three-dimensional models and immersive multimedia methods. The sericulture section displays the sericulture tradition in Hangzhou and surrounding areas since the Song Dynasty.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_silk_museum_sa_03.png'),
  ('中国丝绸博物馆', 3, 'Weaving and Dyeing Gallery (Zhizao Guan)', '织造馆', '<p>The Weaving and Dyeing Gallery is located on the west side of the first floor of the main building of the China National Silk Museum, with a floor area of about 1,000 square meters. It is the core window showcasing China''s core technical prowess as the "Kingdom of Silk." The exhibition is divided into three major sections: "Weaving Techniques," "Dyeing and Printing," and "The Four Famous Brocades." The weaving section displays over a hundred pieces of actual weaving machines and models from the Warring States Period to the Ming and Qing Dynasties. The most impressive is the "Live Weaving Demonstration Area"—sessions at 9:30, 11:00, 14:00, and 15:30 daily—where professional weavers operate reconstructed weaving machines on-site to demonstrate the weaving of kesi, Shu brocade, Yunjin brocade, and Zhuang brocade.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_silk_museum_sa_04.png'),
  ('中国丝绸博物馆', 4, 'Costume Gallery: Magnificent Attire (Fushi Guan: Huamei Fushi)', '服饰馆：华美服饰', '<p>The Costume Gallery is located on the south side of the second floor of the main building of the China National Silk Museum, with a floor area of about 1,500 square meters. It is the largest thematic exhibition hall for textile costuming in China, with the richest collection. The exhibition follows historical chronology, divided into six sections: "Pre-Qin and Two Hans," "Wei, Jin, Southern and Northern Dynasties," "Sui and Tang," "Song and Yuan," "Ming and Qing," and "Modern Times." The collection exceeds 3,000 pieces (sets), including the Western Han plain gauze dan衣 (replica), Tang Dynasty kesi bead-patterned robe, Southern Song velvet quilted robe, Yuan Dynasty gold-threaded cape, Ming Dynasty flying-fish robe, Qing Dynasty court robe, and Republican-era qipao. The exhibition hall employs a combination of scenario reconstruction and mannequin display.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_silk_museum_sa_05.png'),
  ('中国丝绸博物馆', 5, 'Conservation Gallery: Textile Cultural Relic Restoration (Xiufu Guan: Fangzhipin Wenwu Xiufu)', '修复馆：纺织品文物修复', '<p>The Conservation Gallery is located on the north side of the first floor of the main building of the China National Silk Museum, with a floor area of about 600 square meters. It is the only thematic display space for textile cultural relic restoration in China. The gallery opens the restoration workspace to the public—through large glass partition walls, visitors can observe the entire process of conservators cleaning, matching, replenishing, color-fixing, and mounting damaged silk cultural relics, truthfully presenting the "turning decay into wonder" cultural relic regeneration process. The gallery also has a mini exhibition area for "Restoration Achievement Exhibition," periodically updating before-and-after restoration comparison photos and restoration notes. The Conservation Gallery holds a "Face-to-Face with Conservators" activity every Wednesday and Saturday afternoon 14:00-16:00.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_silk_museum_sa_06.png'),
  ('中国丝绸博物馆', 6, 'Brocade and Embroidery Gallery (Jinxiu Lang)', '锦绣廊', '<p>The Brocade and Embroidery Gallery is located in the corridor on the third floor of the main building of the China National Silk Museum. It is a thematic display corridor about 120 meters long and the most visually splendid exhibition space in the entire museum. The corridor takes "Splendid Brocade and Embroidery of China" as its theme, with four major exhibition sections: "Four Famous Brocades," "Renowned Regional Embroideries," "Ethnic Weaving," and "Modern Innovations." The Four Famous Brocades section centrally displays classic works of Nanjing Yunjin, Sichuan Shu Brocade, Suzhou Song Brocade, and Guangxi Zhuang Brocade.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_silk_museum_sa_07.png'),
  ('中国丝绸博物馆', 7, 'Fashion Gallery (Shizhuang Guan)', '时装馆', '<p>The Fashion Gallery is located in a separate building on the east side of the China National Silk Museum, with a floor area of about 1,800 square meters. It was rebuilt and expanded in 2016 and reopened to the public, and is currently the largest textile and fashion thematic exhibition hall in China. The exhibition takes "From Tradition to Modernity" as its main thread, divided into four major sections. The gallery houses over 500 pieces of various fashion items from the late Qing Dynasty and early Republican period to the early 21st century. The Contemporary Designer Works section centrally displays silk-themed works by renowned Chinese and international designers.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_silk_museum_sa_08.png'),
  ('中国丝绸博物馆', 8, 'Xiaofeng Book House and Cultural Creative Space (Xiaofeng Shuwu yu Wenchiuang Kongjian)', '晓风书屋与文创空间', '<p>Xiaofeng Book House and Cultural Creative Space is located on the south side of the first floor of the main building of the China National Silk Museum. It was established in 2018 in cooperation with the Zhejiang Xinhua Bookstore Group, and is currently one of the best-regarded bookish cultural creative complexes in domestic museum cultural creative spaces. The book house covers an area of about 400 square meters, with four major functional spaces. The cultural creative space has jointly developed a series of silk-themed cultural creative products in cooperation with institutions such as the Suzhou Museum and Nanjing Yunjin Museum.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_silk_museum_sa_09.png'),
  ('中国丝绸博物馆', 9, 'Outdoor Garden and Tea Plantation (Huwai Yuanlin yu Chayuan)', '户外园林与茶园', '<p>The Outdoor Garden and Tea Plantation is located on the sloping land south of the China National Silk Museum building complex, covering an area of about 8,000 square meters. It was completed in 2015 synchronously with the museum''s renovation and expansion project, and is currently one of the most exquisitely designed outdoor exhibition spaces among domestic museums. The entire garden is designed according to the layout of classical Jiangnan gardens, with five major functional sections. The mulberry orchard plants over 15 varieties of mulberry trees. The tea plantation plants the Xihu Longjing Quntizhong variety. The garden also scatters multiple groups of bronze sculptures themed "Silk Stories."</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_silk_museum_sa_10.png'),
  ('西湖', 0, 'Duanqiao Canxue (Broken Bridge with Remnant Snow)', '断桥残雪', '<p>Duanqiao (Broken Bridge) is located at the intersection of Beishan Road and Baiti (White Causeway) in Xihu District, Hangzhou. It is the location of "Broken Bridge with Remnant Snow," one of the Ten Scenes of West Lake, and also the bridge with the most romantic color and cultural heritage in Hangzhou. The bridge is a single-arch stone bridge, 8.8 meters long and 8.6 meters wide, first built in the Tang Dynasty, with the existing bridge body reconstructed in 1941. The name "Broken Bridge" originates from folk legend—after snow, when the sun-facing side of the bridge melts while the shaded side remains snow-covered, the bridge body appears broken yet not broken from afar, hence the name "Broken Bridge with Remnant Snow." The bridge is also the classic scene location where Bai Suzhen and Xu Xian met in the "Legend of White Snake."</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_west_lake_sa_01.png'),
  ('西湖', 1, 'Baiti (White Causeway)', '白堤', '<p>Baiti (White Causeway) extends from Broken Bridge in the east to Autumn Moon over Calm Lake in the west, with a total length of about 1 kilometer. It is the most famous spring-viewing causeway at West Lake, alongside Sudi and Yanggongdi known as the "Three Causeways of West Lake." The causeway name "Bai" originates from the beneficial governance achievement of Tang Dynasty poet Bai Juyi, who dredged West Lake and built lake embankments during his tenure as Hangzhou governor (822-824 CE). The sides of the causeway are fully planted with peach trees and weeping willows. Baiti is also an excellent position for viewing the West Lake sunrise.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_west_lake_sa_02.png'),
  ('西湖', 2, 'Pinghu Qiuyue (Autumn Moon over Calm Lake)', '平湖秋月', '<p>Pinghu Qiuyue (Autumn Moon over Calm Lake) is located at the west end of Baiti, on the south foot of Gushan, in Xihu District, Hangzhou. It is one of the Ten Scenes of West Lake and also the most classic venue承载ing (bearing/carrying) the moon-viewing culture of West Lake. The scenic area covers an area of about 2,000 square meters, composed of four parts: the Imperial Stele Pavilion, the Autumn Moon over Calm Lake Tower, the lakefront water-access platform, and the "Zhejiang Tide" artificial rockery group. Every year during the period from the 15th to the 20th day of the 8th lunar month, when the autumn sky is clear and the lake is as calm as a mirror, the bright moon rises from the eastern horizon of the lake, and its reflection falls into the water.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_west_lake_sa_03.png'),
  ('西湖', 3, 'Gushan and Xiling Seal Society (Gushan yu Xiling Yinshe)', '孤山与西泠印社', '<p>Gushan (Solitary Hill) is located on the northwest side of West Lake in Xihu District, Hangzhou, between the west end of Baiti and Xiling Bridge. It is the largest natural island in West Lake, named for being "one mountain in the lake, solitary in the lake''s center." The hill is about 38 meters high, covering about 300 mu, connecting Baiti and Xiling Bridge, forming the unique pattern of "island within the lake, mountain within the island." Gushan is the area with the highest cultural density at West Lake. Among these, Xiling Seal Society was founded in 1904 (30th year of the Guangxu reign of Qing Dynasty) and is the Chinese historical academic organization with the longest history and most profound influence in seal art.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_west_lake_sa_04.png'),
  ('西湖', 4, 'Quyuan Fenghe (Breeze-ruffled Lotus in Winy Courtyard)', '曲院风荷', '<p>Quyuan Fenghe (Breeze-ruffled Lotus in Winy Courtyard) is located south of the intersection of Beishan Road and Yanggongdi in Xihu District, Hangzhou. It is one of the Ten Scenes of West Lake and also the most representative landscape of West Lake in summer. The scenic area covers an area of about 28 hectares, composed of five major sections: Yue Lake, Zhusu Garden, Quyuan, Fenghe (Wind Lotus) Area, and Lakeside Dense Forest Area. The scenic area plants over a hundred varieties of lotus, including precious varieties such as Xihu Red Lotus, Shuguang Lotus, Ancient Lotus, and China-Japan Friendship Lotus. Every year from June to August, the lake surface is covered with blooming lotus and lush lotus leaves.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_west_lake_sa_05.png'),
  ('西湖', 5, 'Sudi Chunxiao (Spring Dawn on Su Causeway)', '苏堤春晓', '<p>Sudi (Su Causeway) is located on the west side of West Lake in Xihu District, Hangzhou, extending from Nanping Mountain in the south to Qixia Ridge in the north, with a total length of about 2.8 kilometers. It is the most famous spring-viewing causeway at West Lake and ranks first among the "Ten Scenes of West Lake." The causeway was constructed in 1090 CE (5th year of the Yuanyou reign of Northern Song) under the supervision of Su Shi (Su Dongpo), then serving as the prefect of Hangzhou.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_west_lake_sa_06.png'),
  ('西湖', 6, 'Huagang Guanyu (Flower Harbor Viewing Fish)', '花港观鱼', '<p>Huagang Guanyu (Flower Harbor Viewing Fish) is located on the west side of the south section of Sudi, on the west bank of West Lake in Xihu District, Hangzhou. It is one of the "Ten Scenes of West Lake" and also the scenic area with the richest ecological charm at West Lake. The scenic area covers about 20 hectares, composed of five major sections: Peony Garden, Red Fish Pond, Flower Harbor, Large Lawn Area, and Dense Forest Area. Red Fish Pond is the core of the scenic area, raising thousands of red carp and koi. The Peony Garden plants over a hundred varieties of peonies and Chinese herbaceous peonies.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_west_lake_sa_07.png'),
  ('西湖', 7, 'Leifeng Pagoda (Leifeng Ta)', '雷峰塔', '<p>Leifeng Pagoda is located at the foot of Xizhao Mountain on the south shore of West Lake in Xihu District, Hangzhou. It is the carrier of "Leifeng in the Sunset Glow," one of the "Ten Scenes of West Lake," and also one of the most iconic structures in the West Lake scenic area. The original pagoda was constructed in 975 CE under the supervision of King Qian Chu of Wuyue Kingdom. On September 25, 1924, the millennial ancient pagoda collapsed with a loud crash due to excessive brick theft. In 2002, driven by the Zhejiang Provincial Government and Hangzhou Municipal Government, the new pagoda was reconstructed on the original site according to the concept of "pagoda covering ruins."</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_west_lake_sa_08.png'),
  ('西湖', 8, 'Nanping WanZhong (Evening Bell from Nanping)', '南屏晚钟', '<p>Nanping Wanzhong (Evening Bell from Nanping) is located inside Jingci Temple at the foot of Nanping Mountain on the south shore of West Lake in Xihu District, Hangzhou. It is one of the "Ten Scenes of West Lake" and also the most Zen-like and culturally profound soundscape of West Lake. Jingci Temple was built in 954 CE during the Wuyue Kingdom period by King Qian Chu of Wuyue, and is a millennial ancient temple second only to Lingyin Temple in the West Lake vicinity. Inside the temple is a bronze great bell weighing about 10 tons and about 3.6 meters high. Every dusk, the temple monks perform evening chanting and strike the evening bell.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_west_lake_sa_09.png'),
  ('西湖', 9, 'Liulang Wenying (Oriole Singing in Willow Waves)', '柳浪闻莺', '<p>Liulang Wenying (Oriole Singing in Willow Waves) is located on the southeast shore of West Lake in Xihu District, Hangzhou, between Qingbo Gate and Yongjin Gate. It is one of the "Ten Scenes of West Lake" and also the open park with the richest natural ecological charm in the West Lake vicinity. The park covers about 21 hectares, composed of four major sections: Friendship Garden, Wenying Garden, Jujing Garden, and Yangfeng Garden. Along the lake shore are planted over ten thousand willow trees of various types. The park also hosts a large number of singing birds such as orioles, hwameis, and larks.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_west_lake_sa_10.png'),
  ('西湖', 10, 'Hubin Park (Lakefront Park)', '湖滨公园', '<p>Hubin Park is located on the east side of West Lake in Xihu District, Hangzhou, between Hubin Road and Nanshan Road. With a total length of about 1.5 kilometers, it is a transitional lakefront park between the West Lake scenic area and the core urban district of Hangzhou, and also the most popular and vibrant civic leisure space in Hangzhou. The park has a lakeside walkway about 15 meters wide along the lake side, flanked by weeping willows, camphor trees, osmanthus, and cherry blossoms——scenery varies across the four seasons. A large-scale musical fountain is set up in the central area of the park, operating on a regular schedule daily with coordinated lighting and music (generally one show each at 19:30 and 20:30), with water jets reaching up to 80 meters high——the night view is especially spectacular. Hubin Park is also the best position for viewing Hangzhou''s urban light show.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_west_lake_sa_11.png'),
  ('西湖', 11, 'Santan Yinyue (Three Pools Mirroring the Moon)', '三潭印月', '<p>Santan Yinyue (Three Pools Mirroring the Moon) is located in the southeastern part of West Lake in Xihu District, Hangzhou. It is the largest island in West Lake, covering an area of about 6 hectares, formed by dredged silt from West Lake, and has long been renowned as the "Number One Scenic Spot of West Lake." The island''s name originates from the three bottle-shaped stone pagodas standing in the lake water south of the island——the Three Pools Stone Pagodas. On bright moon nights, candles are lit inside the pagodas, and the openings are covered with thin paper——candlelight shining through the paper holes onto the lake surface creates the marvelous scene of "moonlight, candlelight, and lake light" reflecting each other, hence the famous name "Three Pools Mirroring the Moon." The island also appears on the back of the one-yuan RMB banknote.</p>', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_west_lake_sa_12.png'),
  ('西湖文化广场', 0, 'West Lake Cultural Square Main Sculpture', '西湖文化广场主雕塑', '', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_west_lake_cultural_plaza_sa_01.png'),
  ('西湖文化广场', 1, 'Zhejiang Provincial Science and Technology Museum', '浙江省科技馆', '', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_west_lake_cultural_plaza_sa_02.png'),
  ('西湖文化广场', 2, 'Zhejiang Natural History Museum (Hangzhou Branch)', '浙江自然博物院（杭州馆）', '', 'https://edwvrriuwzaaqznklrgi.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/cover-images/sub-areas/all/hangzhou_west_lake_cultural_plaza_sa_03.png'),
